title: choctawhatchee coast batter fried shrimp
directions: Sift flour and seasonings.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add beer and mix into dry ingredients, stirring until well blended. Stir in butter.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: *I purchased ready-made pie crust.

title: ceviche
directions: Cut fish in small pieces.
Place in sieve and pour boiling water over it.
Let drain well.
Put all other ingredients in a bowl (not metal) and add fish.
Let cool at room temperature, then cover and put in refrigerator.
Fish must always be covered by lime juice.
It should be prepared about 6 hours before serving.
Serve with salty crackers.

title: buckeyes(makes 190)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Stick a toothpick into each ball and chill on wax paper overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches, sugar and 1 stick butter into a pot; bring to a boil, then add 1 package of biscuits.
Pinch off bits of biscuits and then pour into a large cobbler pan.
Top with the other can of biscuits.
Put other stick of butter on top, then sprinkle with sugar.
Cook until brown.

title: pluck cake
directions: Glaze:
Heat brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon and chopped pecans in saucepan until boiling.

title: barbecue sauce with hot dogs
directions: Cook onion and pepper slowly in oil. Add catsup mixture to pepper and onion.
Pour over split hot dogs and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: crustless pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl, then bake in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 45 minutes.
The crust forms at the bottom.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Melt together over low heat.
Mix thoroughly and spread over frosted brownies.

title: cream gravy
directions: Pour off all except 1/4 cup drippings from skillet in which chicken or other meat was fried.
Place skillet over medium heat, add flour and stir until browned.
Gradually add milk, cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Serve hot.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: old-fashioned hand-churned strawberry ice cream
directions: Hull berries.
Rinse thoroughly and put through a sieve.
Add sugar and light cream.
Whip the thick cream until stiff and blend into mixture.
Pour into cream container of your ice cream maker (prepared with ice and salt according to the specific directions of your freezer).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Chill 1/2 hour.
Form in a ball or log and roll in chopped pecans.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans well. Put in pot with water, ham bone and pieces of ham.
Fill water up to almost cover meat and bone.
Stir and check occasionally.
Have lid half off.
Bring to a boil and then lower to low, cooking for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Pillsbury crescent rolls.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add eggs and
fruit
cocktail. Mix well and pour into pan.
Mix together
cup brown sugar and 1 cup nuts.
Sprinkle on top of cake and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Combine sugar, salt, orange rind and orange juice in a large bowl.
Add walnuts; toss to coat.
Line a large jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Coat with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Spread walnuts evenly over foil.
Bake walnuts in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until dark brown and bubbly, stirring the nuts halfway through.

title: scalloped cabbage and apples
directions: In a greased baking dish place alternate layers of the cabbage and apples.
Season each cabbage layer with salt and butter.
Sprinkle the sugar on the apple layers.
Over the last layer spread the buttered bread crumbs.
Cover and bake in 350 degree oven for about 45 minutes, or until cabbage and apples are tender.
During the last 10 minutes of baking remove the cover so the crumbs can brown.
Serve warm.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Use a 2 1/2-quart crock-pot or 2 1/2-quart pot.
Mix all ingredients in crock on high.
Cook for 2 hours.
Turn crock-pot to low until ready to eat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except sauce and bacon.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan and cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer squash crab casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
With a very low fire, cook onion, zucchini and yellow squash until tender.
Add crab and heat through.
Serve hot.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix yeast and water in large bowl.
When lukewarm, add other ingredients.
Save flour until last.
Mix enough flour for soft dough.
Let rise 60 minutes.
Divide and spread into 2 pizza pans. Add sauce, meat, cheese, etc.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. (Bake slower than prepared crusts.)

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to
a
rolling boil, then add your peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop
by the spoonful on wax paper until cool.

title: crock-pot dove
directions: Season doves with pepper and paprika; coat with flour.
Brown in hot oil in skillet.
Place doves in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 4 hours or on low for 7 to 8 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Bake in 2 layers about 25 minutes at 350° until done.

title: meat ball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons steak sauce. Mix and shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Brown in oil in skillet. Drain fat from skillet.
Combine 1/3 cup steak sauce, brown sugar and butter with meat balls in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen meat balls.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
Blend in flour.
Add ketchup, chili sauce, water and seasonings.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Spoon mixture into buns.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; toss with apples to coat.
Place apple slices in baking dish and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon apples with juices into pastry-lined pie plate. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust, making 2 slits on top for steam to escape.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix well with coconut, sour cream, marshmallows, pineapple chunks and orange slices.
Chill. You may add drained fruit cocktail, if desired.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Place cream cheese in center of glass baking dish.
Pour chili over cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven or microwave until cheese is bubbly and warm through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan heat soup, Cheez Whiz and evaporated milk.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and marshmallows in a pan. Pour over popcorn and enjoy.

title: frozen company salad
directions: Soften cheese and combine with cream until well blended.
Add drained fruit and rest of ingredients, then fold in whipping cream.
Pour in an oblong dish; cover and freeze.
May be frozen in square milk carton, then slice when ready to serve.
Great for Christmas.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and celery salt until almost done.
Drain well.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in a casserole, then add 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Lay 4 or 5 slices of Velveeta cheese over first layer.
Add rest of potatoes and onion.
Spread remaining 1/2 can mushroom soup with 4 or 5 more slices of cheese on top.
Dot top with butter and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop onion and jalapenos into small pieces.
Chop tomatoes after draining seeds and juice.
Cut avocados in half lengthwise and scoop out.
Mix these ingredients in large bowl.
Add crushed garlic and lemon juice.
Chop cilantro into fine pieces.
Add and blend together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: charlie's chicken
directions: Coat chicken halves generously with garlic salt.
Cook over grill on open fire (350°) for 1 hour.
Turn very frequently to keep chicken from burning.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Blend crackers and oleo together for crust.
Arrange crust in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Place berries on crust.
Cover with cheese-sugar mixture.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can use half of mix and 3 ounces cream cheese and place in an 8 or 9-inch store bought graham cracker crust.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in oil in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 3 to 5 hours.

title: apple tacos
directions: Boil sugar, water and margarine.
Place 3 or 4 pieces of apple filling in tortilla.
Roll up and place in casserole dish.
Pour liquid over tortillas.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Baste every 10 minutes.
Let set awhile after removing from oven.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Mix butter in beans.
Mix in almonds. Pour into greased casserole.
Pour cheese over and mix.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pleasure
directions: Place crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour margarine over crumbs; mix well.
Press firmly in bottom of pan.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in small amount salted water.
Don't overcook. Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salad oil, salt and pepper.
Mix and cook until thick, about 15 minutes. Layer carrots, onions and green pepper.
Layer again in casserole. Pour sauce over.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Sift 2 cups flour with baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add remaining 6 cups flour and stir.
Drop shortening by spoonfuls on top of flour mixture.
Cut in or mix at low speed until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Store in airtight container.
When ready to use, spoon into measuring cup (do not sift).
If it becomes lumpy, stir with fork.

title: hawaiian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in 3 tablespoons oil. Brown hamburg and drain fat.
Add sauteed vegetables with hamburg along with the sugar, mushrooms and soy sauce.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in oil; add, while browning, the garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain beef.
Put beef mixture in pot; cook on low until water cooks out.
Add vegetables and another cup of water to beef. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook 5 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cover meat with water.
Add celery seed, onions, sugar and salt.
Cook for 2 hours.
Take up beef and shred, then add Worcestershire sauce and catsup to remaining stock.
Add shredded beef and simmer for as long as you wish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut up or grind chicken.
Add other ingredients; mix.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Stir all together. Refrigerate.

title: oriental cabbage
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Cool.
In frying pan, melt margarine; add almonds, sesame seed and noodles.
Stir constantly until evenly browned; cool.
Chop cabbage and onions; mix well.
Add almond mixture; mix well.
Just before serving, toss with sugar vinegar mixture.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until the surface is golden brown.
The pie will firm up as it cools.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring cherries and sugar to boil.
Add cherry jello.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cider cranberry mold
directions: Bring cider and water to boil in small saucepan.
Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling liquid in large bowl.
Stir in cranberry juice.
Pour into 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Remove from mold.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 6 to 8 servings.

title: german dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix per directions on package in large pan (11 x 14-inch or 14 x 14-inch).
Melt oleo in pan.
Cover with pecans, then coconut.
Pour prepared cake mix over this.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop on cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake frosting
directions: In sauce pan cook cornstarch and water until thick.
Set aside until cool.

title: swiss bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 the onions for topping.
Top casserole with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to package instructions.
Add onions in with noodles when boiling.
Add desired amount of salt.
Drain noodles and onions.
Add soup, cheese, mayonnaise and pimento. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Butter one side of bread and layer on the bottom of a 9x13 baking dish.
Cook sausage until
brown; drain well.
Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, half & half and salt.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator for 15 minutes before baking.
Bake casserole, uncovered for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: vegetable tortellini soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven until tender, about 6 minutes.
Add broth, tomatoes, picante sauce and basil; bring to boil.
Stir in tortellini; simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Continue to simmer 3 to 4 minutes or until tortellini is tender.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 8 servings, about 9 cups of soup.

title: olive balls
directions: Mix flour, cheese and butter together into a dough.
Drain olives.
Make a patty in hand, flatten and wrap around olive. Cover completely, but thin.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, place in plastic bag and store in freezer.
They are ready to bake any time.
Bake frozen.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter; add wine and cook until evaporates.
Make white sauce with remaining butter, flour, tarragon and cream.
Add mushrooms, chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Stack lasagne as follows, noodles, chicken sauce, cheese, with second layer topped with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttery pound cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add eggs and flavor and mix well.
Add butter and sour cream.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1 cup of sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats a spoon.
Allow to cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 9 tablespoons of sugar and beat to soft peaks.
Add to milk mixture.
Add 1 quart of commercial eggnog for additional spices and flavor.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan with butter.
Spread pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cheerios
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until dissolved.
Add peanut butter. Cook until dissolved.
Pour over Cheerios.
Stir.
Let set until cool enough to handle, then roll into balls, then serve.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter, vanilla and egg.
Press in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until light brown.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place chocolate candy on baked layer.
Let stand until soft; spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into about 2 x 1-inch bars while warm. Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: instant rice pilaf
directions: In skillet, saute mushrooms and onions in melted butter until tender.
Add bouillon; bring to a boil.
Add instant rice.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Gently fluff with fork.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and buttermilk, then beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; beat for 3 minutes.
Add food coloring and vanilla flavoring.
Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain any grease.
Add tomatoes, beans and soup.
Break tortillas into small pieces.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and grated cheese.
Layer until you end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot or cheese bubbles.

title: roasted red pepper salad
directions: Place whole peppers on an open grill over a red-hot fire.
Char all sides evenly.
Place in a closed paper bag for 15 minutes. Peel away the charred skin.
Remove the tops and seeds.
Slice into narrow strips and marinate in the olive oil and pepper for at least 30 minutes.
Serve at room temperature on a bed of Italian parsley or a leaf of red lettuce.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Add dressing and ketchup. Grate onion to taste (1/2 to 1 medium onion).
Blend until smooth. Serve with pretzels.

title: wine wieners
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over wieners.
Simmer in crock-pot for 3 hours.

title: venison steaks
directions: Salt and pepper steaks to taste.
May use seasoned salt, if desired.
Coat steaks with flour.
Place steak in skillet with hot oil.
Brown.
Remove from skillet until all are browned.
Place onions and bell peppers into skillet and cook until tender.
Add drained mushrooms.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes more.
Steaks may be returned to pan and allowed to simmer for 10 minutes or onions, peppers and mushrooms may be served as a side dish.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Have meats ground together twice.
Soak breadcrumbs in cream 5 minutes.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Mix meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley, salt, spices and a dash of pepper.
Mix thoroughly until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
(Wet hands or chill mixture first.)
In skillet, brown meatballs in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove meatballs from skillet and prepare gravy.
Return meatballs to gravy.
Cover; cook slowly about 30 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: mixed vegetables casserole
directions: Stir together broccoli vegetable mix, water chestnuts and soup.
Put in a 9 by 13 inch pan.
Mix the cracker crumbs and butter, place next on top.	Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sole veronique
directions: Measure thickness of fish.
In a large skillet, bring broth just to boiling.
Carefully add fish.
Return just to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer gently until fish flakes easily (allow 4 to 6 minutes per 1/2-inch thickness of fish).
Transfer fish to baking dish.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage and remove from skillet.
Saute onion in sausage fat.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in buttered 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Add grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: ultimate chocolate brownie cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine Crisco, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on low speed until creamy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Slowly add milk.
Beat at low speed.
Stir in chips.
Drop dough on ungreased cookie sheet by heaping spoonfuls.
Bake 6 to 9 per sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Will look moist but will firm with cooling.

title: caramels
directions: Cook sugar, butter and white corn syrup for 30 minutes.
Add whipping cream; cook to soft ball stage.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan. Let set overnight.
Cut in small pieces.
Wrap in waxed paper and twist ends.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time and beat well. Add dry ingredients along with milk and flavoring.
Beat 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening and butter until smooth; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Blend on medium speed until creamy. Will cover
one 9 x 13-inch cake or 2 layer cakes.

title: rye bread rounds
directions: Mix all to taste.
Put on rye rounds.
Broil until bubbly.

title: orange cooler
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, water, honey and vanilla in blender; whirl until frothy, gradually adding ice.
Serve at once. Garnish with orange slices and fresh mint.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In large skillet, add to hamburger, chili mix, pepper and onions; simmer for 5 minutes until onions are transparent.
Add tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add macaroni; simmer 10 more minutes.

title: baby pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fry sausage.
Melt cheese into sausage.
Add onion and seasonings.
Stir thoroughly.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze 24 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in plastic bags.
Store in freezer until ready to use.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.
Serves 40.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven or deep casserole dish, mix rice and mushroom soup.
Pepper chicken and place on top of rice.
Pour French onion soup over all.
Cover casserole. Bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Cover each piece with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Cover completely.
Place 1/2 in Bundt pan. Melt oleo; pour over bottom half.
Add rest of biscuits; pour rest of butter over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes and flip pan.

title: baked fish with lemon and black pepper
directions: Place fish fillets into a medium sized bowl and sprinkle with salt, turmeric, cumin, black pepper and garlic, tossing to coat well.
Cover and marinate for 50 to 60 minutes in the refrigerator.

title: mother's lemon freeze
directions: Butter loaf pan.
Line bottom and sides with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well the evaporated milk, refrigerated overnight, with sugar.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pan over crust. Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Put in freezer.
Slice to serve.

title: wine slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large container.
Pour 1/4 c. Powdered Sugar over it and stir well.
Freeze overnight.
Take out right before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly and pour batter into greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from pan immediately.
Pour hot glaze over cake.

title: frozen salad or dessert
directions: Mix well and put into foil muffin cups and freeze. Makes approx. 30 cups.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Boil onions until tender.
Place layers of onions, bread crumbs and butter in casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover all with milk and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: roasted carrots
directions: Cook carrots, water, sugar and salt together until tender. Drain.
Cool.
Dip carrots into butter, then into crumbs.
Place on greased baking tray.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine and press into loaf pan or casserole dish.
Mix with mixer, cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and box of sugar until well blended.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Be sure to cool before slicing.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water.
Add the strawberries; break apart.
Add the crushed pineapple.
Chill until set in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together the Cool Whip, softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream; spread on top of jello.
Chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight or parboil.
Cook at 325° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cheeseburger pie(the pie that makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick until smooth, 1 minute with handbeater.
Pour over beef and onions in pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: candy quick
directions: Melt Candy Quick.
Add peanut butter over double boiler.
Set for 5 minutes.
Mix everything else in.
Put on wax paper by teaspoon.
Put in refrigerator until firm, about 1/2 to 1 hour. Makes about 60.

title: sopaipilla
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix yeast in warm water.
Melt shortening in scalded milk.
Combine all ingredients; knead until smooth and glossy.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Knead and roll dough 1/4-inch thick. Cut into 3-inch squares.
Drop into very hot 450° oil.
Remove after each square has puffed up and lightly browned.
Cut small hole in each and fill with honey.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello.
Let cool.
Fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; spread on baked bread. Sprinkle remaining ingredients over top of cream cheese mixture. Prepare and serve the same day.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; stir in oleo.
Add sugars, eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown and white sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat.
Sift flour, salt and soda and stir in.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop the batter from a teaspoon well apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and water.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and raisins; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Strip top.
Bake at 350° until crust is done.

title: quick 'n easy cookie bars
directions: Combine graham crackers, flour and baking soda.
Set aside. Combine melted oleo and brown sugar; stir in eggs, water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over warm surface.
Let stand until chips soften.
Spread evenly.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely in medium bowl after they have been boiled in jackets and peeled.
Set aside.

In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup of butter until almost melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in potatoes and turn into a greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle on paprika for color. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shorty's chicken and rice dressing
directions: Place dry rice in bottom of baking dish; pour broth over. Next celery, onion, bell pepper and cream of chicken.
Place chicken over top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over.
Cover with foil; let bake for 2 hours or until tender.
Uncover last 10 minutes so chicken can brown.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Cook in iron skillet sprayed with Pam.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery until tender.
In a small amount of water, add garlic and all other ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta salad(named for its bright colors)
directions: Chop vegetables into small bite-size pieces.
Cut tomatoes and Cheddar cheese into small cubes.
Mix everything together and marinate thoroughly with a bottle of Italian dressing.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
Mix vegetables a few times.
Serve chilled. Great for hot summer days!

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and ball out and fry until done.

title: chop suey
directions: Fill a Dutch oven or very large saucepan 1/4 the way up with water.
Put on stove and add onions and celery.
Cook 15 minutes on medium heat.
When a little soft, add bean sprouts.
Cook for about 20 minutes more, then add soy sauce, a bay leaf and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 10 minutes and add cornstarch mixed with water to thicken (4 or 5 tablespoons cornstarch and water). Serve on hamburg rolls.

title: tuna dip
directions: Sprinkle dry dressing mix over tuna.
Mix in sour cream. Serve cold with crackers.

title: cool turkey pitas
directions: Combine turkey, celery, apple, raisins and yogurt in medium bowl.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place one lettuce leaf in each pita half.
Fill breads with turkey mixture, dividing evenly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: master baking mix
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar 3 times.
Cut in the shortening until the mixture is the consistency of cornmeal.
Stir in the dry milk powder.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
To measure baking mix, pile lightly into a cup and level off with spatula.

title: mini-cheese cakes(makes 12)
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese and sugar on medium speed until well-blended.
Add eggs, mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill. Top with fruit preserve, nut or chocolate.
Be creative.
Actual size is cupcake size.

title: meatless chili
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter in a large pot until transparent.
Add canned ingredients and chili seasoning.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.

title: garden salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Let set.
Partly gel.
Add vegetables.
Pour in mold.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar. Add and beat well, eggs, sour milk and vanilla. Stir in flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Add zucchini and nuts. Spoon into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle chips on top. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: washbasin cookies
directions: Step 1:
In your largest bowl or Dutch oven, stir together flour, wheat flakes, sugars, coconut, pecans, rolled oats, baking soda and salt.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce.
With fork, blend sauce with hot water.
Add cup of cold water and all other ingredients.
Pour into container.
Refrigerate until firm. Based on 12 servings, per serving 133 calories; fat 3 grams.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Form into loaf; put in shallow 7 x 10-inch pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over loaf. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jeanne's chicken
directions: Heat in saucepan and stir until smooth.
Dip chicken pieces in sauce.
Place in baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and baste with sauce.
Bake about 1/2 hour more until done.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Make up one gallon of tea.
Add juices and other ingredients to tea in a large pot.
Simmer until hot.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; pour into 12 x 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with tidbits and margarine.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, flour, sugar, coconut and oleo.
Pat 1/2 the mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the pie filling on top of crust; sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until coconut is browned.

title: idaho oven fries
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/8-inch thickness.
Pour melted butter on large cookie sheet.
Add potato slices to pan, turning to coat with butter.
Season and bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender (slightly browned).

title: best herbed pork roast
directions: Rub the roast with the tarragon and other herbs, pepper and salt.
Pour vinegar over the roast.
Roast in a 200° to 250° oven for 4 hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff with sugar and salt. Beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and beat until very stiff.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven at 375° and turn oven off. Remove cookies the next morning.

title: double chocolate mint bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir together flour, sugars, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat in eggs and 1/4 teaspoon mint extract; spread into pan.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes or until toothpick is inserted and comes out clean.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Fold all together in a shallow baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until set in the middle at 350°.

title: hartzog's tea room applesauce muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Fill paper lined tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate. Serve cold.
Serve over salad greens.

title: mexican beef and rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs.
Stir in corn during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Shape meat into six 1/2-inch thick patties.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well, chill and then drain off excess liquid before serving.

title: cheesy jalapeno new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover in a large saucepan 20 minutes or until tender; drain. Cool and cut into thin slices; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Cream together the Cheddar and 1 pack of cream cheese.
Work this with fingers until smooth. Add rest of cheese and continue to work with hands until creamy. Add onions.
Mix well.
Chill; shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts and parsley.

title: palacinky(slovak pancakes)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and 1 cup of the milk.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in flour and remaining milk.
Continue beating until very smooth.
Pour 1/2 cup batter into a hot, greased, medium sized skillet.
Tilt skillet to spread batter over entire bottom.
Fry on each side until brown.
Spread with jelly, jam, cottage cheese or any desired filling; roll up.
Yields 20 to 25 pancakes.

title: durham's favorite crunchy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together (it is easier to do with hands). Form dough into several rolls.
Wrap each in waxed paper.
Chill.
Slice cookies. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes, depending on how crunchy and done you like your cookies.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Mix egg in water.
Wet pecan in this mixture.
Coat well.
Mix salt, sugar and cinnamon together.
Coat pecans well.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes on 300°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chicken-corn casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water for 7 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is slightly browned.

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese stand until it reaches room temperature, so that it will be easy to mix and spread.
If using onion, dice into tiny pieces.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: Puree strawberries until smooth.
Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until the sugar is dissolved. Combine sugar mixture, strawberries and lemon juice.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices and whole strawberries, as desired.
Yield: approximately 1 1/2 quarts.

title: homemade strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix well and pour into an oblong pan.
Bake at 375° until done.
Can use 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: honey bun cake(by steven)
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil by hand.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans or raisins.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cover with rest of cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple delight\(dessert)
directions: Pinch up angle food cake in small pieces over container. Spoon in 1 (16 ounce) crushed pineapple.
Cover all cake.
Mix box of vanilla pudding as directed and pour over crushed pineapple. Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add Cool Whip and serve.

title: helene's cookies
directions: Cook 10 minutes.
Stir.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over 2 heaping cups Rice Krispies.
Roll in coconut or nut meats.

title: prune muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, spices, nuts and prunes and set aside.
In a second bowl, mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Pour all liquid ingredients over dry ingredients and mix just enough to blend together.
Spoon into 18 greased 2 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until brown and springy to touch.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 325.
Place pie crust in 9 inch pie pan.
In a large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs, beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread evenly in crust lined pan.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes or until deep golden brown and filling is set.
Cool at least 1 hour.

title: erwtensoep(green pea soup)
directions: Thoroughly wash the split peas.
In a large heavy pot, combine the split peas, pig's feet, ham and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat, skimming off the foam and scum as they rise to the surface.
Reduce the heat to low; partially cover the pan and simmer for 3 hours.
Add the salt, onions, celery tops, celery root and carrots and simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.
(If the ham is salty, you may wish to reduce the salt.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mash with fork (need 2 cups). Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine squash, cheese, pimento, onion and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Heat milk to boiling, allow to cool slightly, then stir into mixture.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in the oleo.
Cook until limp.
Add the cooked rice, broccoli, Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Mix all ingredients into a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top for the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: breakfast
directions: Mix bisquick and oregano, then add milk, oil and eggs; mix lightly.
Add meat and cheese.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan:
cake mix, egg and melted oleo.

title: homemade popsicles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Store in closed container.
To make 1 batch, mix 6 tablespoons to dry mix in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Pour into popsicle molds or Dixie cups.
Freeze.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan until just tender; drain.
Layer potatoes and next 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cabbage gumbo
directions: Fry meat in shortening, add onion.
Saute.
Add cabbage, cover with water, add pepper pod, cook until tender.
(Careful about adding too much water.)

title: easy roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and picante sauce until blended, spread on the tortillas, roll up.

title: mississippi chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cream sugar and butter. Beat egg yolks into mixture one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk and chocolate, ending with chocolate.
Add vanilla; do not overbeat. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: heavenly egg shrimp
directions: Saute shrimp, onions and bell pepper in butter until vegetables are soft and shrimp is pink.
Beat eggs and milk together and add to skillet.
Scramble until soft and set.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves four.
(Crawfish, lobster or crab meat can be substituted.)

title: ice cream pie
directions: Make graham cracker crust with crackers and butter.
Grease pie plate.
Put in freezer.
Melt large size Hershey bar with almonds in double boiler.
Add strong coffee to melted chocolate. Pour into crust and put in freezer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add ice cream (any flavor you want), 1 pint to 1 quart.
Top with sprinkles.

title: cream cheese and chutney spread
directions: Put chutney in blender and blend until smooth. Mix with other ingredients and allow chilling in refrigerator. Serve with crackers of choice.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Let stand while you cream fat, sugar and egg. Then add whole milk into which you have poured the hot water. When tepid, add yeast mixture, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and flour. Knead until smooth and let rise until double in size. Shape into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. This can be kept in refrigerator for a week.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake until done.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix the large container of Cool Whip with the pie filling that has been prepared according to instructions on box.
Layer the crackers, then the Cool Whip and pie filling (vanilla) that have been mixed together.
Repeat, then put the cherry pie filling on top.
You can use any pie filling.

title: punch
directions: Boil together the sugar and water until it is very thick like a thin syrup.
Add the orange juice, bananas, pineapple juice (mixed and frozen in 1/2-gallon container).
Thaw the juice at least 2 hours.
Pour into large bowl.
Add 2 liter bottle of ginger ale.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 3 well-greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut stem off eggplant and slice lengthwise in 1/2-inch strips. Place in greased 8-inch square baking dish, overlapping the strips.
Combine the tomatoes, tomato juice, oats, oat bran, spices and garlic.
Spread over the eggplant.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4, 159 calories per serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed.
Pour in greased and floured long baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. While cake is still warm, spread marshmallow cream over top, then frost.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour.

title: halibut in sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put halibut in baking pan.
Place sliced butter, chopped onion and sliced lemon on top.
Cover entire fillet with sour cream.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes, then remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bachelor dave's corn chowder
directions: Chop onion, cube potato and place all ingredients, except milk, into saucepan.
Put over medium flame; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are soft.
Add milk; simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Depending on appetite, serves 1 to 4. Season to taste.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix chopped apples with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add beaten eggs, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Fold in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add raisins.
Nuts (3/4 cup) can also be added, if you like.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all the ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook and brown bacon and hamburger.
Drain. Add all other ingredients; mix well. Simmer 1 hour, then bake 40 minutes at 300°.
(Drain some of the beans.)

title: herb butter
directions: In a small bowl, cream together the butter, the chives, the parsley, tarragon, mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Let the butter stand, covered, in a cool place for 1 hour to allow the flavors to develop.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter and place in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or glass dish.
Cover butter with walnuts, then add chocolate chips. Cover chocolate chips with coconut.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Cover coconut with milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked stew
directions: Place all ingredients in order given, in baking pan with a tight fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: easy martha washington chocolate cake
directions: Stir together cake mix, eggs and water.
Fold in cherry pie filling.
Bake as directed.
May be put into layer cake pans.

title: rice consomme(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Brown butter, onion and rice until golden brown (not burned). Stir frequently! Put in baking dish and pour 2 cans beef consomme over. Cover casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello to cake mix, then add eggs, oil and water; beat well.
Add strawberries.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake about 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Check with toothpick to test if done.

title: wild grape catsup
directions: Cook grapes on low until soft, about 1/2 hour, then put through sieve.
Take grape puree and cook with rest of ingredients.
Bottle and seal.
Store in a cool, dry place.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until moist.
Do not use mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Finally, add bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on cooling racks. Cool completely before frosting.

title: florentine mushrooms
directions: Defrost frozen spinach; drain the excess water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean and trim stems from mushrooms.
Save stems for another use.
Place mushroom caps in a 4-quart pot. Add water until caps are covered and bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes, until caps turn a light brown.
Drain and pat dry on paper towels.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl and mix together.
Add 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper and mix together.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spreading smoothly over casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup of butter (melted) with potato chips. Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in a big bowl; stir in sour cream, onion and cheese.
Melt margarine and stir in soup.
Mix into hash browns. Melt another 1/2 stick margarine and stir in 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes or crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small casseroles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour angel food pan.
Boil potato to make 1/2 cup mashed, set aside to cool.
Sift together next 7 ingredients.
Cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Slowly add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add milk. When fully mixed, add mashed potato.
Mix in vanilla, raisins and chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pan and bake approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Whip sugar and Crisco until mixed.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well after each.
Add extract, then add flour.
Mix well. Bake at 350°.
Start with cold oven.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Thicken pudding in reserved fruit juice.
Blend until smooth and add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place flour in bag. Add chicken a few pieces at a time. Shake to coat; repeat with remaining chicken. Heat oil in large skillet. Add chicken. Brown over medium heat. Remove from pan; set aside. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Saut over medium heat until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, salt and oregano, stirring to crush whole tomatoes. Place chicken pieces on top of tomato mixture. Cover. Reduce heat to simmer. Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Serve with hot noodles or rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the
margarine,
peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Pour mixture
over
the
Crispix and let cool somewhat. Put powdered sugar
in
a
bag.
Add the mix and shake. Keeps well in a plastic container.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add the flavorings and mix well.
Pour half the batter in a 10-inch tube pan.
Mix the cinnamon and brown sugar in a bowl. Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not open oven door until done.

title: easy sugar and spice nuts
directions: Add brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and water to melted butter.
Stir in the nuts until coated.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 4 to 5 minutes until nuts are toasted and glazed. Spread in single layer on waxed paper until cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Enjoy!

title: hazelnut balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grind hazelnuts very fine.
Empty into mixing bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients, except confectioners sugar, to nuts and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate dough at least one-half hour.
Form into 1-inch balls; place one-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes, until set but not brown.
Cool partially on cooling rack and roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: busy day pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and set aside.
Add about 1/2 c. of water to skillet and scrape up meat particles.
In a crock-pot place a layer of meat, a layer of dressing; repeat.
Pour water from skillet over top.
Cover and cook on high for 2 hours or on low for 4 hours.

title: turkey bonnets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange turkey in 5 portions in ungreased baking dish.
Combine soup, milk and chopped pimento strips.
Pour over turkey.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat in oven until warm and bubbly.
Separate dough into 5 biscuits.
Place one on each portion of turkey.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add milk to corn.
Add flour, sifted with salt, pepper and baking powder.
Add oleo and well beaten eggs.
Beat all together well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 Tbsp. flour and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Coat meat with mixture.
Heat skillet with 2 Tbsp. butter; add meat.
Cook round steak or sirloin for about 20 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is about half done, 3-4 minutes and put into bowl.
In pan, add 2 Tbsp. butter, 3 Tbsp. flour and paste.
Stir in cold beef broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly, return the browned meat and other ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and wine. Cook slowly till heated and serve over noodles.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix wet ingredients together and add dry mix; mix well.
If mixture is too thick, add a little milk.
Drop by big spoon on Teflon pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Time may vary.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve 1 box raspberry gelatin in 2 cups hot water and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set up.
Dissolve plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat condensed milk and sugar; do not boil.
Mix in gelatin mixture; add vanilla, cream cheese and nuts.
Pour over first layer and let set up.
Dissolve remaining raspberry gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add blueberry pie filling and pour over second layer.
Let set up.

title: wilma's zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together).
Mix in zucchini and chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Frost when cool.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Rinse; combine with cabbage, carrots, pepper, onion and tuna.
Blend mayonnaise with remaining ingredients.
Toss and chill.
Serve over lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tiny chocolate cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease miniature muffin pans with butter.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon chocolate crumbs into each muffin cup.
Beat cream cheese at high speed until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Spoon 1 teaspoon into each muffin cup.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire racks 5 minutes.
Can be prepared 2 days ahead or frozen for 1 month.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: brenda's taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rigatoni greek style
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and chopped chicken.
Cook until onions are soft and chicken tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups broth; bring to boil.
Meanwhile, stir together remaining 1/4 cup broth with cornstarch.
Add to boiling broth.
Cool 1 minute.
(Remove from heat.
This may be made a day ahead and refrigerated.)

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cut away thick stem and base of cauliflower, separate flowerets, wash and chop coarsely.
Combine the chicken stock and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Simmer cauliflower in stock until tender.
Melt butter in 4-quart saucepan, stir in flour and cook over low heat, do not allow flour to brown.
Pour in stock and the milk, beating constantly with a whisk.
Cook, stirring until mixture is smooth and somewhat thick.
Add the salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour soup into a food mill and process until smooth. Return puree to pan, beat the egg yolks with a fork, then beat in 1/2 cup of hot puree very slowly.
Now whisk the mixture back into the saucepan and cook over moderate heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not let it boil or it will separate.
Add the lemon juice and taste for seasoning.
You may substitute the cauliflower with broccoli or potatoes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and other ingredients, stirring constantly, about 7 minutes.

title: fruited ice tea
directions: Let tea steep in boiling water.
Remove tea bags and add sugar; add frozen juices and enough water to make a gallon of tea. Serve over rice with a sprig of mint added.

title: company chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender, saving 1 3/4 cups of broth.
Melt butter in broth.
Set aside.
Cut up chicken into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken. Top with dry dressing, then pour broth over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, covered or uncovered.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of flour mix. Combine egg, oil and milk. Add to the dry ingredients. Stir until moistened. Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir into batter with lemon peel.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Dip muffins into warm butter and sugar.

title: drizzle topped brownies(about 20 brownies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
In medium mixing bowl, combine baking mix, sugar and cocoa.
Mix with spoon or fork until thoroughly blended.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely. Prepare Quick Vanilla Glaze.
Drizzle onto cooled brownies.
Cut into bars.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and add milk a little at the time. Beat and then add vanilla and lemon juice.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in a cold oven.

title: patsy's lemon cream cheese frosting
directions: Empty all boxes in a mixing bowl.
Add Parkay (or butter), cream cheese and water.
Blend on medium speed of mixer until fluffy.
Add lemon extract and yellow food coloring.
Blend well for about 1 minute.
Frosts a 3 layer cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Measure a cup of love, a real old fashioned, heart felt love and stir briskly into the hearts of two people, called husband and wife.
Add a generous amount of dreams and hopes, and when the children come along, measure out generous portions of understanding and tenderness.

Add random spoonfuls of gaiety and laugher, mixed thoroughly with a pinch of kindness and sympathy. Fold in three cups of loving discipline, and for flavor, add a good portion of paternal firmness to keep the concoction from falling apart.
Then season with reverence for each other and a tablespoon of sympathy.
Sprinkle faith in Christ generously over the mixture and moisten with tears of love.

And, if you have followed the recipe carefully, been patient in carefully measuring the ingredients, and will exercise Christian patience, the result will be a home blessed with the peace of God and a serenity unknown to those who try to achieve a happy home haphazardly.
The results:
A lovely establishment that too few in the world are privileged to enjoy.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute celery, onion and pepper for 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, rice, crab meat, shrimp, pimento and soup.
Place in greased casserole; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
If mixture seems a little dry before baking, add reserved liquid from mushrooms.
This dish freezes well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place meat in casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper and chopped onions.
Mix soup and milk, pour over meat.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: coffee punch
directions: Pour coffee over ice cream and beat lightly until partially melted.
Add teaspoon of creme de cacao.
Pour into punch glasses; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until sugar completely dissolves and no granules are visible.
Add Pet milk and Eagle Brand milk, salt, vanilla and 2 cups milk.
Mix well and pour into 4-quart freezer.
Add milk to fill line.
May add 2 cups fresh ripe fruit to mixture for different summer flavors.

title: taco meat filling and homemade taco sauce
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is browned (add 1/3 cup water if you use ground turkey; brown and drain off water).
Add garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili powder and tomato sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon into taco shells and top with taco sauce (make ahead of time).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into loaf pan and bake one hour at 350°.

title: sun tea
directions: Fill gallon glass container with cold water.
Put tea bags in water.
Cover jug with lid.
Screw lid on tight.
Take it outside in bright sunshine.
When it's the color you like you have sun tea.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all
together,
except
coconut.
Shape
into ball, cover with thin layer of pepper jelly and then coconut.
Chill 24 hours. Top with cherry.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mashed potatoes, melted butter and salt.
Mix well.
Add soda to sour milk; combine both mixtures together.
Add baking powder, nutmeg and flour; mix all ingredients well.
Put part of dough on floured board; do not have dough too soft.
This makes about 40 medium sized doughnuts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms in salted water. Remove stems and dry. Mince stems, spring onions and garlic. Saute in butter. Add bread crumbs until all moisture is absorbed. Add egg to mix. Oil mushroom caps and fill with mixture. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes. Serve while warm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into small pieces and place in a large bowl.
In a jar, combine all remaining ingredients except bacon and eggs. Shake until mixed well and pour over spinach.
Toss lightly. Garnish with crumbled bacon and egg slices.
Serve immediately.

title: "easy" chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, mix oil, sugar, chocolate and eggs with a mixing spoon.
Add water and dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla.
Stir well until smooth. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: angel pudding
directions: Chill jello mixture and whip.
Add whipped milk.
Mix with jello mixture.
Roll graham crackers to a fine mixture; line dish with 1/2 of them.
Pour in pudding; sprinkle remaining crackers on top.
Set in refrigerator to chill.

title: fried chicken wings
directions: You will also need a large frying pan and a plastic or paper bag.

title: umsteads' dump cake
directions: Spray baking pan with vegetable oil.
Pour in crushed pineapple.
Spread thinly, then pour in cherry pie filling and mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top of mixture.
Pour on cake mix and smooth over evenly.
Sprinkle the nuts over mixture, then pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Will not need refrigeration.
May sit on table until it's all gone.
It won't last two days; at least at my house or at Mt.
Level it won't.
Enjoy and try it soon.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, sugar, cornstarch, crushed pineapple and juice and red food coloring.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add the dry jello.
Stir well and allow to cool.
Add sliced bananas and nuts (if desired).
Pour into pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: ms. cora's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, mix well after each egg.
Alternate adding flour and whipping cream to mixture until all ingredients are mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°
in a prepared Bundt pan.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Cook brisket on rack in pan of water (1/2 pound per person). Cool meat and slice.
In large saucepan, mix remaining ingredients and warm, then coat meat with mixture.

title: whipped pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into crusts.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with remaining Cool Whip before serving. Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger,
chopped
onion
and
green	pepper. Drain. Put in
2	quart casserole dish.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over hamburger.
Add layer of cheese, then layer of Tater Tots.
Bake
at
350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; work in butter so that it's doughy like pie crust.
Add wet ingredients and keep adding flour as needed. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
This recipe is used for cutout holiday cookies.

title: praline pecan loaf
directions: Mix together and place in bottom of cake pan.
Set aside.

title: lennie's christmas breakfast
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 14-inch pan with the hash browns and pour beaten eggs, flour and milk over.
Layer rest of ingredients over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9-inch tube pan. Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Peel, core and finely chop apples.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, gelatine, salt and spices in saucepan. Separate eggs.
Add yolks to milk and add to the dry ingredients in pan.
Cook on medium to low heat until it comes to a boil and thickens.
Stir constantly as this scorches quickly.
Remove from heat and stir in the pumpkin.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour pumpkin mixture into crust.
Garnish with whipped cream at serving time. Makes deep 9-inch pie.

title: poor man's salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Mix well again and refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix and make 5 rolls the shape of salami.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap 8 beans in a bacon slice and place seam side down in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Arrange more bean bundles in dish until all are used.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.	Stir in beaten egg, water and vanilla.	Add sifted dry ingredients, rolled oats and chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: creamed chicken over cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, mushroom soup and pimiento; cook, stirring constantly, just until thoroughly heated.

title: pineapple angel cake
directions: Follow package directions for mixing and baking cake except substitute the undrained pineapple for water (20 oz. can).	Pour mixture into ungreased 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until top of cake is golden and cracks appear.	Let sit for 10 minutes; then turn out on rack and let cool.
Mix the undrained pineapple (8 oz.) and the pudding, fold in the whipped topping.
Frost cooled cake whole, or use a topping on individual servings.
Makes 12 servings.

title: microwave pudding and pie filling
directions: Use large bowl.
Microwave on High the milk until warm (2 minutes).
Mix and add to milk the sugar and flour.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Blend together egg yolks, milk, vanilla and margarine. Mix well and pour into milk mixture; whisk together.
Cook for 1 minute intervals until custard is thick, stirring between each minute of cooking.
Cook and pour in cooked pastry shell.
Top with meringue or whipped topping if desired.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut a horizontal slit in each pork chop to form pocket.
Mix in a bowl the butter, apple, stuffing mix, cheese, celery, onion, raisins, orange juice and salt; mix well.
Fill each pocket with stuffing mix.
Secure opening with toothpicks.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch microwavable dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and water. Brush on pork chops.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook at Medium for 17 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla, and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins, pineapple and nuts.
Blend well.
Bake in a greased and floured bundt pan at 325 degrees for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or in 2 greased and floured bread pans for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Brown meat and onion in a skillet until done.
Drain off excess grease. Alternate layers of zucchini, meat mixture and 1 3/4 cups of cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
Serves 4 to 6. Very good!

title: chapman chicken curry
directions: Cook chicken in water (1/2 quart) with salt and pepper.
Cool and debone.
Saute onion, celery, and apples in olive oil until soft; stir in curry and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup of chow mein noodles, the tuna, celery, cashews (if wanted), onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with drained canned Mandarin orange sections.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.
If you double recipe, bake in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in syrup, eggs and flour thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cut up tamales.
Add corn and chili, mix well.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add olives in rows. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: apple waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nutmeats in a serving bowl.
In a saucepan, stir together sugar, flour, egg and 2 tablespoons water. Add 1 cup water and butter.
Bring to boil; cook until thickened. Stirring, add vinegar and salt.
Let cool.
Pour over mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: holiday chocolate butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except flour and cocoa.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy (2 to 3 minutes).
Gradually add flour and cocoa until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls as desired (1-inch balls, 2 to 3-inch logs, balls flattened, balls with indentations, cookie press like spritz, etc.).
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until set.
Cool. Decorate with melted chocolate chips, melted almond bark, nuts, colored sugars, candied fruit, candies, maraschino cherries, etc. Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and coconut; stir well.
Reserve 3/4 cup dough for topping.
Spread remaining dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread apricot preserves over mixture; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into bars.

title: chocolate candy bar pie
directions: Shell:
Melt margarine and mix with wafers.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: mike beck's famous green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, milk, mushroom soup, cheese and 1/2 can French onions.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with remaining French onions and bake additional five minutes.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: eggplant espana
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in slices and soak in salt water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Boil eggplant until tender; drain well.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Drain skillet, except for about 1 tablespoon of fat.
Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat.
Add the stewed tomatoes; simmer.
Add eggplant, then cornbread dressing and crumbled bacon.
Heat this mixture slightly.
Add 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into a greased baking dish; sprinkle the top with the remaining cheese.
Decorate with the Fritos.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
This freezes well, or may be kept in the refrigerator for hours without the Fritos.
If frozen, thaw slightly before baking.
Serves 6.

title: homemade penrose
directions: Trim ends of hot dogs, then cut each into 4 or 5 pieces. Combine vinegar, water, salt, sugar and pepper sauce in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs. Simmer, do not boil, for 30 minutes.
Put in jar. Cover and let stand 2 to 4 days. Drain and serve.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: spinach ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 60 balls.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: deviled crab cakes
directions: Melt oleo in shallow pan.
Add onion and cook until softened (not brown).
Put in flour.
Remove from stove and blend in boiled milk.
Add beaten egg.
Reheat until thickened and well blended. Add crabmeat.
Cool and form into cakes.
Dip patties into 1 beaten egg or more if needed.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven
to 450° (hot); melt butter in oven in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Remove from oven when butter is melted. Sift dry
ingredients
into bowl;
add milk, stir slowly with fork until
dough
just
clings
together (about 30 strokes). Turn out on well floured board.
Knead lightly about 10 times, roll
out 1/2-inch thick into rectangle, 12 x 8-inch.
Cut in half lengthwise,
then
crosswise
into
16 strips.
Dip each strip on both sides in melted butter.
Place close together in 2
rows. Bake
15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In greased casserole, layer uncooked potatoes, onions and combined flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat.
Sprinkle paprika over all.
Cut butter into small pieces and spread over casserole ingredients.
Pour scalded milk over all.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes covered.
Remove cover.
Stir.
Cook uncovered for approximately 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender and milk is absorbed.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook yams until tender.
Mash potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and beat with a mixer.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle miniature marshmallows over top and return to oven until slightly brown.

title: quick chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine.
Add chicken, soup and chicken and noodles dinner. Turn into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy vegetable stir fry
directions: In large skillet, stir fry vegetables in margarine until crisp tender. Reduce heat. Add Velveeta, milk and marjoram; stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Serve over rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot-applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
With whisk, beat the eggs.
Stir in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add applesauce and carrots; mix well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring to moisten.
Fold in raisins and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Pour into greased pan or pans.
Sprinkle on remaining walnuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.

title: tea cake receipt(100 years old)
directions: There
were no baking directions, as this was my grandmother's recipe that she gave to my mother when she married in 1918!
All mother
told
me was that you mix just like you do any cookie
or cake
mix
and bake in a medium oven.
If they don't do
right, turn the oven up or down (as needed).
Grandmother used a wood stove and my mother used a gas oven.

title: fudge sauce a la rosey
directions: Mix Carnation,	sugar and chocolate in saucepan.
Bring to boil over
medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring vigorously. Remove from
heat.	Add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater for 1 minute.
Serve hot	or chilled on ice cream or cake.
If the sauce seems a
bit too thick, just add undiluted Carnation and blend before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except crackers, in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crush crackers into small crumbs and sprinkle over
top
of
casserole.
Bake
at
375° for 30 to 40 minutes until hot all the way through.
Serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook meat and onion well and drain.
Heat a large iron skillet and add 1/4 cup of oil.
Sprinkle corn meal in bottom of pan to keep cornbread from sticking.
Pour 1/2 of the cornbread mixture in bottom of pan, then layer meat, jalapenos and cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread mixture on top and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie(like pecan)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped pecans or walnuts on top.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.

title: villa valenti's linguine and red clam sauce
directions: Remove 12 of the clams from their shells and save them along with their liquor until later.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a large saucepan.
Mix in milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute; stir.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats; stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine (or butter) until mixture clings together.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat eggs, granulated sugar, lemon peel and juice.
Beat about 5 minutes.
Add 4 tablespoons flour and baking powder to egg mixture.
Blend just until moistened.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sift powdered sugar over top.
Cool, cut into bars.

title: self-fill cupcakes
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and then add next four in order.
Fill cupcake holders 1/2 full.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, shortening, baking powder and soda together, then take out 1 cup crumbs for top.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased cake pan. Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake.

title: apple raisin salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add to the Cool Whip and beat with mixer.
Then add diced apples and raisins.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen buttermilk ice cream
directions: Add sugar to mixture until it becomes very sweet. Just keep tasting to get it to suit your taste. Mixture is then ready for freezing in ice cream freezer.

title: sausage and egg breakfast
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned and crumbled.
Drain well.
Combine sausage, eggs, milk, cheese and salt.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: graham cracker streusel cake
directions: Mix in one bowl the graham cracker crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Set aside.

title: greek-style potatoes with lemon & thyme
directions: *Preferably small new potatoes such as Yellow Finns, Yukon Gold, Bintjes or red-skinned potatoes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and slice pickles.
Pack in jars.
Put in each jar 2 garlic cubes, 1 bunch of
dill
and
1 grape leaf.
Bring to boil the water, vinegar
and salt.
Pour over pickles and cold pack 5 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares and serve hot or at room temperature.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Serve 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup hot water.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison and pork.
Add onions, peppers, garlic and chili peppers until sauteed.
Add red cooking wine, chili mix and chili beans.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Add Maza flour for thickening. Some folks add brown sugar or molasses.
It's your call.

title: banana pineapple salad
directions: Let mixture (first 6 ingredients) cool.
Then pour over the pineapple chunks, bananas, apples, marshmallows and coconut.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water, crushed pineapple and 1 can pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour into plastic gallon milk jugs; do not fill completely to allow for expanding.
Freeze.
Set jugs out 1 to 2 1/2 hours or until mixture is mushy.
