At serving time, add ginger ale, sherbet and additional can of pineapple juice.

title: low-fat banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add dry ingredients except for chocolate chips.
Once well blended, stir in chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoon-size balls of dough onto cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In small bowl, mix cocoa, vinegar and red food coloring.
In large bowl, beat sugar, eggs and shortening.
Mix in contents from small bowl; mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and soda.
Gradually add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Makes 3 (9-inch) round layers. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: moist oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, water, raisins, shortening, spices, salt and nuts.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Set aside to get quite cool.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, oats and soda to the cooled mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet or ungreased nonstick sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: wild rice and chicken breast
directions: Mix rice well and spread in heavy buttered deep dish.
Pour broth over rice slowly.
Scatter mushrooms and chestnuts over rice.
Place breasts over this using 6 or 8 breasts.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over each breast, then salt and pepper.
Dilute mushroom soup a bit with milk or cream and put a spoonful on each breast.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover pan with foil and cook for 1 hour at 400°.
Remove foil and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers with 1 stick oleo and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, 2 sticks oleo and eggs together with mixer; beat on high speed for 15 minutes.
Spread this mixture on top of vanilla wafers, then put drained pineapple on top of egg mixture.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Cover and chill overnight.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Place bread and cheese alternately in a casserole dish.
Beat eggs, milk, and salt together; pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl.
Drain salmon; remove skin and bones and flake.
Add salmon, bread, salt and butter to eggs.
Heat milk to lukewarm and add to salmon mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn off of cob.
Cut onions, peppers and celery into small cubes.
Mix everything together and boil all together until soft.
Seal in jars.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Spray a deep 9x13 in. dish with pam.
Un-roll 1 can crescent rolls and spread on bottom of pan.
Cover with 1/2 of bacon and 1/2 of sausage.
Pour 1/2 eggs over meat.
Add 1/2 bag of cheese and cover with 1 can of crescent rolls.
Add other 1/2 of bacon and sausage and cover with other 1/2 of egg mixture.
Top this with balance of cheese.
Top with last can of crescent rolls. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour three times with baking powder, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add orange rind, nuts and dates.
Last, fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crispix mix
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels on low heat until liquid forms.
Mix in Crispix until coated.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until Crispix is completely covered with chocolate.
Spread mixture on wax paper until "dry" (sheen disappears).

title: smoked sausage and corny bean soup
directions: Place oleo, onion and garlic in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Add water, potatoes, sausage and beans.
Stir in beef bouillon.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, corn, catsup, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes more.

title: spice nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°). Add nuts and vanilla.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Cool. Separate.

title: eggnog
directions: Heat milk in large saucepan until hot but not boiling.
While milk is heating, beat together eggs and salt in a large bowl, gradually adding the sugar.
Gradually stir the hot milk into the egg mixture; transfer back to the saucepan and cook on medium-low heat, stirring constantly with a whisk, until the mixture has thickened or coats the spoon.
(Thermometer should register 160°.) Stir in vanilla, cool quickly by setting pan in bowl of ice cold water and stirring for about 10 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: taco style spuds
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a 10-inch skillet, cook ground beef, shredded carrot and sliced green onion until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Stir in water, tomato paste, chili powder, oregano and garlic powder.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add onions, garlic, celery and green peppers.
Add water with bouillon cubes.
Add cornstarch dissolved in 1/4 cup of water.
Cook about 30 minutes on low.

title: pepperoni macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Cook sausage and onion.
In a large bowl combine pizza sauce, tomato sauce, and milk.
Stir in sausage mixture, macaroni, pepperoni, and mushrooms.
Transfer to a greased 9x13 baking dish.
Cover, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10-15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice in a bowl, add pudding mix and Tang and mix well.
Stir in pineapple chunks and fruit cocktail; mix and chill, adding the banana chunks before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; put in casserole.
Cook for 8 minutes at 350°.
Mix together Jell-O, strawberries and water; put in refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar; put on pretzel crust after it has been cooked.
Put congealed strawberry mixture on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put half of potato mix in pan; put half of cheese over this.
Add rest of potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and add rest of cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes more until brown on top.
May add ham chunks.

title: leftover turkey, ham or chicken casserole
directions: Arrange meat in ungreased baking dish.
Top with hot broccoli, cover with cheese, stir together milk and soup and pour over cheese.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: creamy garden spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute broccoli, zucchini, mushrooms and carrot in oil until crisp-tender. Remove from heat and set aside. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. In another saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in the flour, bouillon and thyme until blended. Gradually add milk; bring to a boil. Cook, stirring for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat to low; stir in cheeses until melted.
Add the vegetables and heat through. Drain the spaghetti and toss with the vegetable mixture. Serves 4.

title: mrs. racke's applesauce
directions: Put all the ingredients in a pan and cook on medium for 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Mash with a potato masher. This freezes well!

title: chicken crepes
directions: Spread rolls out flat. Place chicken on large end of rolls and roll up.
Butter casserole dish.
Place rolls in dish, not touching one another.
Add undiluted soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Beat constantly with mixer for 7 to 10 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Remove immediately from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: fudge krispies
directions: *Also a good way to use Easter bunnies!

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and give to children.
They can mold dough into their own creations and then eat.
Great afternoon activity and snack.

title: lentil ham soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take meat off bone and mix with lentils.

title: french silk cream pie
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and continue beating. Add chocolate and vanilla. Continue beating. Drop in 1 whole egg at a time. After each egg, beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream and almonds. Chill.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together the coconut and nuts. Put into bottom of 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Prepare cake mix according to box directions and pour over coconut and pecans. Place margarine and cream cheese in microwave or saucepan; heat until softened. Stir in the confectioners sugar. Spoon over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fast chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, garlic powder and grated Parmesan cheese together. Roll chicken breast in dry mixture and place on a baking stone. Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes. Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until top feels done.
Do not overcook.
No frosting is necessary but use if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf with sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all this as regular meat loaf.
Bake.

title: oatmeal crisps cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Form dough in rolls, 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear wrap.
Chill thoroughly.
With sharp knife slice cookies about 1/2 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at about 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: non-alcohol punch
directions: Scoop 1 quart of lime sherbert into a punch bowl.
Add 12 (7 oz.) bottles of 7-Up, pouring liquid slowly down side of bowl. Add vanilla ice cream and pint of lime sherbert.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream and water in pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered sheet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove skin and debone chicken.
Prepare dressing according to directions.
Layer dressing on bottom of baking dish, then layer chicken, then broccoli.
Pour soup, thinned with 1/2 can water over all.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine rice and next 6 ingredients; mix well. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; top with chicken breasts.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add green beans, then the soups over top of the green beans.
Next, add the Tater Tots and sprinkle with the seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a jelly roll pan in a 375°
oven.
Add single layer of potatoes, cut lengthwise in 1/2-inch slices.
Turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes or until done and tops are crisp.

title: red punch
directions: Makes 1 gallon (approximately 32 punch cups).

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar, creaming until mixture is smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating. Add vanilla. Fold in sour cream and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Shut off oven and leave cake in for 1 or 2 hours or until oven is cooled.
Refrigerate until ready to serve and enjoy!

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and beat for 3 minutes on low to medium speed.
Pour into tube pan which has been greased and floured, or lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Leave in pan until cool to touch.
Turn out of pan.

title: yeast sopaipillas(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add cooled milk.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add liquid.
Work into dough.
Knead dough 15 to 20 times and set aside for 10 minutes.
Add liquid shortening to skillet and heat to 420°.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick; cut in squares or triangles.

title: creamed chicken in patty shells(quick)
directions: Bake patty shells as directed on package.
Heat butter in pan. Add chicken, soup, sherry and mushrooms; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve in shells.
Top with pecan halves; sprinkle with paprika.

title: snow pods and chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, ginger and garlic.
Add chicken and marinate for 1/2 hour.
Heat wok or skillet to medium-high. Stir-fry vegetables and chicken, one at a time, and remove.
Add chicken broth, snow peas and chestnuts to wok.
Heat to boiling.

title: muffuletta salad
directions: Muffuletta salad:
Cook pasta shells according to pkg. directions until firm but tender, Drain well, rinse with cold water, drain well again.
Place pasta in a large bowl.
Add the Provolone, Salami, Mortadella, ham, olives, onions, celery, parsley, thyme and garlic.
Toss until well blended.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Thaw pie crusts overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut pie crusts for 9 x 3 x 11-inch pan, leaving enough crust for 1 layer and top crust after placing in bottom of pan and sides.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon on crust in bottom.
Spoon in 1 1/2 cans of filling. Spread evenly.
Place layer of crust and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Spoon in remaining filling.
Place top crust and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: jello ring
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple, strawberries and nuts.
Pour 1/2 in mold and set in refrigerator to congeal.* (I use the Tupperware mold with removable center.)
Spread sour cream on jello and add other half of jello.
Congeal and serve.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, melted butter, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Put mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with more cheese. (Freezes well.)

title: hostess hollandiase sauce
directions: Beat the eggs well in the top of a double boiler.
Have the butter at room temperature and cream it with the flour.
Add seasoning and lemon juice; then add hot water and stir until smooth.
Pour the mixture into the eggs, set over boiling water and stir until thickened.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in big bowl as if kneading dough. Press into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or shape into loaf.

title: cappuccino
directions: Dissolve coffee in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour into cups.
Top with whipped cream and dash with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Fold cream into coffee until frothy.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: *I use pork chops.

title: oven fried buttermilk chicken
directions: Place buttermilk in shallow dish. On waxed paper or plate, mix flour, poultry seasoning if desired, paprika and salt. Dip chicken in buttermilk to coat completely. Dredge in flour mixture to cover completely. Place on clean sheet of waxed paper. In foil-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, melt butter in a 425° oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly. Spread evenly. Place chicken, skin side down, in pan. Bake* chicken at 425° for 30 minutes. Carefully turn chicken over. Bake 30 minutes more or until internal juices of chicken run clear.

title: salad
directions: Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put over other ingredients.
Keeps in fridge for days.

title: chocolate-covered mints
directions: Mix
confectioners sugar, butter, warm water and oil of peppermint;
form into flat patties.
If soft, refrigerate for about
hour.
Melt
unsweetened chocolate and paraffin wax. Keep
chocolate-paraffin
mixture
over
warm
water.
Place peppermint patties on fork, dip and place on wax paper.
Allow chocolate to set at room temperature.
Makes 5 dozen mints.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and brown sugar to eggs.
Sift together baking soda, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in zucchini, vanilla, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: imagination cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except coconut. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in an 8 x 8-inch pan in microwave.
In a saucepan, bring fruit, 1 cup sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Drizzle over oleo.
Pour fruit on top.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Prepare small meatballs of hamburger.
Fry meatballs until done.
Drain well.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour all 4 cans of soup into a large bowl.
Add 2 envelopes of dried onion soup.
Mix well, then add this mixture to meatballs.
With a large spoon, turn this mixture into meatballs until it is mixed well and meatballs are coated with mixture.
Cook on high for 1 1/2 hours.
Then cook for 1 1/2 hours on low.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: In small bowl, combine sugar, milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater on lowest speed, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping and spread on cooled cake immediately. Refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups or covers 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: maple nut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In open roasting pan, melt margarine in oven.
Stir in brown sugar and maple extract.
Gradually add cereals and nuts if desired, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil and let cool.
Mix with lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add bananas.
To one quart of liquid add 1 quart of ginger ale or strawberry soda.

title: cranberry fig bars
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberries, figs and honey.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes or until cranberries pop. Stir often.
Stir in vanilla.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend together in blender, using pepper of choice.

title: tortellini or ravioli with ham and cream sauce
directions: Simmer heavy cream and butter and greens in pan very slowly until it cooks off a bit.
Add ham; simmer a bit more.
A great addition, if you are so inclined, is a touch of cognac, during the simmering process.
Add your cooked tortellini or ravioli and mix in a good handful of fresh Parmesan or similar grating cheese.

title: salsa cheese dip
directions: Heat salsa in pan.
Add cheese and onion.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheesy chicken enchilada bake
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Add cheese and milk. Reduce heat.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add chicken and olives; mix.
Dip tortillas in hot oil and drain on paper towels.
Place at least 1/4 cup chicken mixture in tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in pan.
You can melt more cheese to pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend shortening into flour as you would when making biscuits, working until they resemble corn meal.
Beat egg yolks and add milk.
Beat together thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and beat only until the two are blended.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake until light goes out on waffle iron.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mary's krustyes
directions: Break eggs into bowl; add vanilla, liquor, baking powder and salt.
Add flour, a little at a time, to mixture.
Mix by hand until dough gets like a pie dough.
Let stand in cool place for 15 minutes.
Roll dough out very thin.
Cut into strips and cut hole in center; pull one end through to make a tie.
Fry in deep hot lard.
Drain lard off as it becomes too brown.
Drain cookies on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: patricia's cucumber sandwiches
directions: Spread each slice of bread with mayonnaise.
Top with cucumber slice and generous dab of horseradish sauce.
Garnish with 1/2 stuffed olive, stuffing side up.
Makes 30.

title: five-pound icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in dish and let chill in refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep popped popcorn warm in low oven.
Combine the brown sugar, butter and syrup and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Pour over popped corn; mix and place in large roasting pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes; mash with mixer.
Add the vanilla, eggs, sugar and melted margarine.
Put in casserole dish.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and salt to taste.
Roll in flour until covered and place in deep pan and pour 1/2 cup chicken broth and add remainder of broth and bake 30 more minutes or until tender and brown.
Bake in 300° oven.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Separate dough into 8 triangles, with points to the center of a 12-inch greased pizza pan.
Press seams to form a crust.
Sprinkle sausage over dough, then hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas with chicken and mushroom soup
directions: Fry up ground beef, pour off fat.
Add onions and bell peppers and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Place small amount of meat mixture into each tortilla and roll up and set aside.
Mix soups and pour over rolled tortillas.
Top with rest of grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes until hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, form into loaf.
Crease down center and add the rest of tomatoes from can (no juice).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: Boil giblets until tender.
Remove and save water for stock. Chop liver and giblets.
Add oil to skillet and brown ground pork and gizzards about 6 minutes.
Add seasoning, onion, celery, garlic and bell pepper; stir thoroughly.
Add butter and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add stock.
Add rice, livers, green onions and parsley.
Stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Cover and lower heat to the lowest heat.
Cook until rice is fluffy.
Enjoy!
Ca Cest Bon.

title: eggnog bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease Bundt pan and press chopped nuts and candied cherries on bottom and sides of pan. Combine cake mix, butter, nutmeg, eggs, egg nog and rum flavoring. Beat until smooth for 5 minutes. Pour into pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes, until cake tests done with toothpick. Cool 10 minutes and invert on dish (cake plate). Dust with powdered sugar, if desired or make a glaze with powdered sugar and milk but don't make glaze real thin.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a greased baking dish.
Combine soups and milk and pour over hash browns.
Stir together.
Lay cheese slices on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cut up chicken and boil for 15 minutes.
Bake cornbread.
Cut up onions; crumble up cornbread.
Take up chicken and use the broth.
Put cornbread in pan.
Pour broth over and put in onions. Sprinkle in sage.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cut up eggs and place around dressing.
Put sliced celery around dressing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook, bone and chunk chicken.
Saute diced celery and onion in melted margarine.
Add soup, broth and mushrooms.
Season with salt, plenty of pepper and Tabasco, if desired.
Add chicken and simmer.
Pour over cooked spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch casserole. May be kept in refrigerator a day or so.
Can be frozen.
Heat in 325° oven until bubbly hot.
Top with cheese and heat until melted.

title: cheesy chicken crescent sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except rolls and egg.
Mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto one end of each rectangle.
Fold dough in half over mixture; press edges to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Brown beef and onion.
Mix rest of ingredients and put in large casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil for a few minutes.
Stir in beef and saute until done.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce, water, kidney beans (drained) and all seasonings.
Cover and cook over low or simmer in crock-pot.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain grease. Stir in pepperoni and sauce.
Add noodles.
Warm on stove until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine garbanzos, pinto beans, green beans, onion and celery. Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and chill 4 hours.

title: beet relish
directions: Grate or mince beets.
In casserole or other container with a cover, mix beets with remaining ingredients.
Cover; store in refrigerator for at least 1 day before serving.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, sugar and cream in mixer.
If marshmallows are used, melt with butter on low heat.
Mix together and beat until smooth.
Pour in baking dish.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers.
Place in jars; also place fresh dill and grape leaves in jar (2 or 3 leaves per quart).
Bring to boil vinegar, water and salt and pour over cucumbers; seal while hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, milk and vinegar until just starts to boil. Remove from heat and cool.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and celery seed.
Stir and mix with potatoes and a small onion.

title: rolled pork loin supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread deboned pork loin.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and marjoram.
Roll and tie securely.
Rub lightly with more marjoram. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Top with a few dabs of butter.
Place on sheet of foil on an open pan.
Bake, uncovered, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until tender.
(To avoid excessive browning, cover loosely with foil the first 2 hours; uncover the last hour.)
Last hour, you can add halved potatoes alongside meat, turning after 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg together.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir both together and blend well.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart and flatten.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare any flavor batter from cake mix batter for cupcakes.
Pour batter into flat-bottomed waffle ice cream cones, filling only 1/2 full.
Set onto baking pan and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool, frost and decorate.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Put the meat into a large saucepan with all ingredients except cabbage.
Cover with cold water and bring to the boil; then skim off any scum.
Cover and simmer very gently for 3/4 hour, then put in cabbage, trimmed and cut into quarters.
Leave a little of the stump on, as this adds flavor.
Cook meat for 30 minutes per pound and serve on dish, surrounded with cabbage.
(The dry mustard powder always makes the beef tender and moist).

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While baking, combine next 5 ingredients. Pour over baked crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: beef stew
directions: Dilute soup with water.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Cover tightly and bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: chocolate cake doughnuts
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Combine milk, melted butter and melted chocolate.
Add flour mixture and milk mixture alternately to egg mixture.
Beat until just blended after each addition. Cover and chill 2 hours.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for about 1 minute per side, turning once.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a glass 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread pineapple and its juice as the first layer.
For the second layer, spread the pie filling.
The third layer, sprinkle dry cake mix.

The fourth layer, slice and lay the butter pats on top of the dry cake mix. The fifth layer, sprinkle finely chopped pecans over mix and butter pats. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° to 375° according to your oven. Should be lightly browned, but not dry is the best.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make an attractive ring mold of orange juice or lemonade, adding seasonal fruits for garnish.

title: chicken kiev
directions: In small bowl, combine butter, chives, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper; mix until blended.
Spoon onto plastic wrap; shape into 2 inch squares.
Freeze 30 minutes.
With melt mallet, pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness; sprinkle with lemon juice. Cut butter into 8 pieces.
Place one in center of each chicken breast half.
Fold short sides of each chicken piece over butter; roll up starting at one long side to cover butter completely. Secure with several short wooden toothpicks.
On large plate combine crumbs, thyme and remaining salt and pepper.
On another plate, place flour.
In bowl, with fork, beat egg with water.
Coat chicken first with flour, shaking off excess, then with egg and then with crumb mixture.
In nonstick skillet heat half the oil over medium heat.
Place half the prepared chicken breasts, seam side up, in pan.
Saute 5 to 6 minutes on each side, until cooked through.
Remove to paper towels to drain; repeat with remaining oil and chicken.
Remove picks.
Serve.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute chuck until brown. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread half of the noodles.
Cover noodles with cheese mixture.
Layer rest of noodles over cheese mixture.
Pour melted butter over noodles, then layer tomato-meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: In large bowl combine cake mix, one egg, margarine and 2 tsp pumpkin pie spice.
Mix on low speed.
Press into greased 10 x 13 baking dish.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix together in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over turkey/fruit mixture.
Top with almonds.
Add 2 cups rice to make this stretch.

title: hot halloween punch
directions: Mix everything together well.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup and add boiling water before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: On the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with taco Doritos chips. Put ground beef in skillet; fry. Drain grease.
Take dry enchilada mix and add to hamburger.
Add water and refried beans. Simmer until thick.
Pour over taco chips in pan.
Add grated Cheddar cheese over hamburger mixture.
Pour mild taco sauce over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: elegant meat loaf
directions: Combine onion soup mix with sour cream and add the eggs. Mix in with beef and sprinkle in bread crumbs. Shape into loaf and bake in loaf pan. Put 2 strips of bacon on top and bake in oven at 500° (preheated), turning heat down to 375° and bake for 1 hour. Serve with fresh mushroom sauce on your meat loaf.

title: breaded okra
directions: Slice okra and dip in evaporated milk.
Roll in meal and deep fry in medium-hot oil. Cook small amount at a time.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter and sugar.
Add pineapple.
Pour over bread.
Stir a little.
Put in a casserole.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Tastes great with ham.

title: mom's apple pal
directions: Place apples in buttered glass pie dish; sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut margarine into sugar mixture.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
The little ones love this one!

title: molded raw cranberry and apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Combine cranberries and sugar. Stir into hot gelatin mixture. Cool. Add apples and celery.
Pour into large mold or individual molds.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.
Unmold.
Serve with mayonnaise and a garnish of lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: eggs casserole
directions: First, saute onions and celery.
Using an egg slicer, slice the eggs, setting aside 6 to 8 of the nice slices for garnish. Set aside 2 to 3 slices of bacon for garnishing and chop the remaining bacon slices.
Set aside paprika and bread crumbs for garnishing.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together; add remaining ingredients. Cook, covered, in a 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: bread pudding #2
directions: Butter baking dish.
Toast bread and butter.
Cut bread into squares.
Beat eggs and add milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread and let stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat and potato loaf
directions: Mix together very well.
Roll into meatballs the size of walnuts.
Cook in spaghetti sauce or bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix egg yolks, vegetable oil, milk, salt, sugar, food coloring and self-rising flour until batter is right consistency.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to batter.
Cook in slightly buttered electric skillet.

title: pancit
directions: Soak mushrooms	in
water;
cut
into strips when soft. Cut pork and
chicken
into
pieces (chop suey pieces).
Slice shrimp into thirds.
To about 4 quarts of boiling water, add a dash of salt
and
a
teaspoon of vegetable oil.
Add noodles; cook until done,
stirring
at
least	every 5 minutes so they don't stick to pot.
Rinse
noodles under cold water;
drain. Brown pork with garlic
in	a wok.	When liquid from meat has evaporated, brown meat
in
its
oil	for
half a minute.
Add dried mushrooms and 4
tablespoons
of patis and stir.	Add a little water;
simmer until liquid evaporates again.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: *Nestea with lemon may be substituted; just omit 1/2 cup lemon juice.

title: blender lemon pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend on high speed for 20 seconds.
Place mixture in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Put in a loaf pan.
Spread tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered in salted water until fork tender, about 40 minutes. Peel warm potatoes and slice. Meanwhile, in large skillet, cook bacon; remove all fat except 1/4 cup. Stir flour into fat in skillet. Add sugar, butter, salt, pepper, vinegar and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, stirring. Remove from heat; add sour cream. Add potatoes, onion and half of bacon; toss gently. Sprinkle with rest of bacon and parsley. Good served warm or cold.

title: sauce for cocktail wieners
directions: Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly melts.
Add mustard. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cocktail wieners, or cut regular hot dogs in 1-inch pieces.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
With rolling pin, roll bread as thin as possible.
With electric mixer, mix thoroughly the grated Cheddar cheese, softened cream cheese and egg.
Spread mixture on bread.
Put 1 asparagus spear on each slice of bread and roll up. (One can of asparagus spears yields about 15 to 22 spears.)
Roll each in melted butter.
Freeze!
While frozen, slice in thirds and bake until crisp, for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat salsa dip
directions: Mix ingredients then refrigerate overnight.
Great dip for corn chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet.
Fry until completely done and drain.
Layer the bottom of a 13x9 inch baking dish with the sausage.
Scramble the eggs.
Layer sausage and eggs.
Top eggs with a layer of shredded cheese.
Finally, top it off with a layer of the Bisquick.
(Note:
To fix Bisquick layer, follow the recipe for biscuits.)
Place in oven and bake at 350° until top layer is golden brown.

title: tomato chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Remove excess fat.
Mix lemon juice, salt, pepper, celery salt, garlic powder and Italian seasoning together. Place chicken in a dish and pour mixture over breast halves. Marinate at least 1 hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and combine all ingredients.
Bake for 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Put crushed potato chips on top before baking.

title: e-z grapefruit cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Crumble 3 to 4 grapefruit sections and add to frosting.
Spread on cooled cake. Garnish top with remaining grapefruit sections and cherries. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Condiments needed: Guacamole salad, salsa, shredded lettuce, shredded cheese, sour cream and jalapenos.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed cucumber rings
directions: Cut cucumbers in half crosswise; remove centers with a spoon. Chill cucumbers until crisp and firm.
Combine remaining ingredients; pack in cucumbers firmly.

title: aunt donna's best cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion.
Cover with water and add salt.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Pour off water.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add seed.
Pour over cucumbers and onion; mix well.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Cover and bake 40 to
60 minutes (or until rice is done) at 350°.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up (or remove skin) in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham dip
directions: Chop ham fine.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk, fold in large Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over grahams.
Cover with another layer of grahams.
Spread remaining mixture over that and top with graham crackers and frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: sweet n' sour ribs
directions: Cook ribs in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Pour off fat and mix all other ingredients and pour over ribs.
Baste and cook 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spider webs
directions: Simple, fun Halloween treat that children can make in a jiffy. Cover 2 cookie
sheets
with
wax	paper.	Arrange the pretzel sticks into 6 groups of
8 on the wax paper.
Shape to resemble spokes of a wheel.	Cut
each
block of candy coating in half. Place in microwavable
glass
dish	and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir
until
smooth,
getting
out
all lumps. Spoon a small amount of
melted
candy into the middle of each group of pretzels.
Spoon a	thin
stream
of
candy around in circles to form the strands
of
the webs.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes. Remove for wax paper.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Blend and bake with Pam coated utensil.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off all fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, or until mixture is the consistency of spaghetti sauce.

title: microwave cranberries
directions: Wash cranberries in cold water.
Drain.
In large glass bowl mix cranberries with sugar and cinnamon.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High setting 4 minutes.
Stir, recover and microwave for 3 more minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir to dissolve.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Mix well.
Add nuts. Mix again.
Pour into mold and set in refrigerator to jell.
When ready to serve, mix together cream cheese (room temperature and creamed) and sour cream.
Spread over top of the unmolded jello.

title: cold cucumber pickles
directions: Mix ingredients and stir well.
Add to clean cucumbers in crock and cover.
Weight cover down.

title: fergie's potato salad
directions: Mix green pepper, small carrot, celery, sweet pickles, onions, radishes, salt, pepper, sugar and pickle juice in mixing bowl. Add small cubes of potatoes to bowl.
Stir and mix with other ingredients.
Add one chopped or diced hard-boiled egg.
Stir. Add mustard, stir and mix with long prong fork and big spoon.
Add mayonnaise as directed.
Stir with fork and big spoon.
Add dry leaves for decoration if desired.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: smooth chili
directions: Cook chili as directed on package; then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Stir often because it will stick.
Serve over Fritos.
This makes a big pot.

title: potatoes ala jean williamson
directions: Spray an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide all ingredients into 3 parts.
Arrange 1 layer of potatoes with salt and pepper to taste, mince garlic, cheese and soup.
Repeat all ingredients to make three layers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 90 minutes.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Wash vegetables.
Drain well.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Add raisins, onions, bacon and seeds.
Cream sugar, mayonnaise, sour cream and vinegar.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: third bread
directions: Mix in order as given.
Knead on a floured board (surface). Let rise.
Punch down.
Divide and bake in 2 loaf pans or may be baked in a Bundt pan.
Let the dough rise in pans before baking. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until done and brown.
Butter tops.

title: five bean barbecue
directions: Drain all beans, except Campbell's.
Before adding bacon, crumble it.
Add bacon and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza(the pepperoni makes it taste really good)
directions: Roll the dough into a circle, then you bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.
Then you put the tomato sauce, the Mozzarella cheese on top and the pepperoni.
Then you bake it again for 15 minutes at 300° because the dough may start to burn.
And then you eat it.

title: hawaiian marinated steak
directions: Use an 8 ounce glass for this marinade.

title: fusilli with vodka sauce
directions: Soak chili in vodka 24 hours.
Combine cream, butter and tomatoes in saucepan.
Simmer until reduced by 1/3, about 12 minutes.
Cook pasta to medium firmness.
Drain well.
Add to sauce.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes.
Mix in cheese and parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: sue gander's apricot salad
directions: Stir together gelatin, hot water and sugar.
Add cream cheese. Beat with an electric mixer while hot, until thoroughly mixed. Chill mixture until practically set.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and mixed topping. Pour into an oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until set.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 can onion rings with drained vegetables, soup and milk. Top with rest of onion rings and grated cheese. Bake in medium oven until heated through.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer.
Serve hot.

title: italian bow tie bake
directions: Cook noodles. Mix with sauce and seasoning. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, granulated sugar and baking soda together.
Add fruit cocktail and eggs.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Can be served plain with whipped cream, ice cream or "thin" cornstarch pudding.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: liver dish
directions: Combine tomato juice and soy sauce.
Pour over diced beef liver.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cook onions in nonstick skillet until tender. Add liver mixture and add potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender. Add green peas.
Simmer about 5 minutes longer. Serve with hot bread.

title: swedish rolls
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a bowl and mix like pie dough. In another bowl, soften dry yeast in warm water, then add eggs (beaten) and milk.
Add yeast mixture to dry ingredients and beat well.
Add 1 cup unsifted flour and stir until well mixed.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, allow 4 hours for dough to come to room temperature.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in wedges and roll from large end to small end.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheezy broccoli
directions: Place unopened package of broccoli in microwave oven. Microwave at High (10) for 4 to 5 minutes, turning over after 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg.
Blend.
Slice peeled apples into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of apples.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake approximately 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat
in	skillet; drain and put in a large Dutch oven. Add
other	ingredients.
Simmer
over
low heat for as many hours as	you
can,
but	no
less than 3.
As your sauce boils down, add
more
water,
however	your
sauce should be thick.
You
may freeze
sauce after it is cooked.	It tastes even better if cooked a day before it is served.
When reheating, add a little catsup.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Cube cheese; put chilies on top of cheese.
Put eggs on top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut in squares.
Can be served on Tostitos.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar, pears, vanilla and nuts.
Add to dry ingredients stirring until just moistened.
Spoon mixture into two greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
May be frozen.

title: hamburger or sausage casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper (drain).
Cook macaroni and cheese according to box directions.
Mix meat, macaroni and cheese, corn and tomato sauce.
Pour into oblong 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fluffy stuff salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello until blended.	Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with maraschino cherries, nuts or Mandarin oranges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain, then add all ingredients.
Mix well in a large bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: summer tuna lunch
directions: Break tuna into coarse pieces with fork.
Mix all ingredients and tuna together.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put ingredients into a buttered casserole dish.

title: knights in shining armour(method:  foil packet)
directions: Slice large onion.
Drain liquid from potatoes; set aside. Shape hamburger into four 1/4-pound patties.

With shiny side of foil face up, place a hamburger patty, 1 to 2 slices of onion, 1 teaspoon of dry gravy mix, 1/3 cup sliced potatoes, 1/3 cup mixed vegetables and 1 to 2 tablespoons of the potato liquid.
Wrap, using the drugstore wrap method.
Place on coals for 10 to 15 minutes per side.

title: island style chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil in large skillet.
Drain excess oil.
Add water and bouillon, green pepper, vinegar, garlic, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Simmer slowly until pepper is tender.
Add pineapple (undrained).
Add 1/2 cup water and cornstarch (mixed together) to thicken sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Beat the eggs in a bowl; dip chicken breasts in, then roll in breadcrumbs.
In a large frying pan with a little bit of oil, fry the chicken breasts until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and put aside.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; beat with mixer.
Spread one package rolls on bottom of pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top and spread evenly.
Place other package of rolls on top of this.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture on top of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: old hickory's boiled cabbage
directions: Place the ham hock in a kettle of water and cook for about one hour.
Add the cabbage, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until nearly dry.
Just before taking up, add 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Be sure to serve with cornbread.
It is good reheated again.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt
oleo and marshmallows together.
Mix all other ingredients with first mixture.
Place in mold pan.
Chill; slice thin.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Add water to apricot juice to make 1 cup, if necessary.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and orange peel.
Add juice; cook until thick.
Pour over sweet potatoes; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; use juice to dilute mushroom soup to make a sauce.
Mix all together; top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian rice balls "arancini"
directions: Mix cooked rice, cheese, eggs, parsley and 1/2 the bread crumbs in a large bowl; add salt and pepper to taste.
Form balls by hand. Roll the rice balls in the remaining bread crumbs.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a heavy pan.
Fry the rice balls, turning them often so they brown.
When crispy and brown, remove and drain on a paper towel. They can be topped with tomato sauce or melted cheese.

title: country fruit bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil and sugar.
Then add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Add all dry ingredients.
Bake in three small loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Add nuts if desired.

title: tomato cheese dip
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute slowly until tender.
Add tomato juice and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add grated cheese; stir over very low heat until cheese is melted and blended with tomato juice mixture.
Keep hot in chafing dish.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Peel the stalk part of broccoli and cut with the flowers, quite fine.
Add celery, onions, bacon and red and green grapes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened.
Add jello to hot mixture.
Cool. Layer strawberries in pie shell.
Pour filling over berries and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and egg together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Chill 30 minutes.
Pour cooled jello over all.
I pour it onto a spoon so it won't go down under.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Pam and flour the bottom of the pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on the top before baking.

title: cheesecake(easy)
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream, sugar and vanilla; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with favorite topping.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine thoroughly in blender.
Refrigerate until used.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut leek in half lengthwise; wash and trim, leaving 2 to 3 inches of green tops intact.
Cut leek halves crosswise into thin slices.
Place in small saucepan; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain; reserve leek.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook until chicken is golden, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach and leek to chicken mixture; cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Spoon chicken mixture into pie crust.
Sprinkle flour and cheese over chicken mixture.
Combine eggs, half and half, brandy, salt, pepper and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: giant shell lasagne(low-fat)
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Cook turkey in a bowl in microwave. Cover bowl with wax paper and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Drain.
In a large bowl, add spaghetti sauce and turkey.
In another bowl, blend Ricotta cheese, Egg Beaters and 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken on the couch
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water as directed on package.
Drain and arrange in shallow baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Simmer chicken in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and cut into bite-size pieces and arrange on broccoli.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over the top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter and pour on brown bread crumbs, then sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 3 people.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine until
crumbly.
Pat into bottom of dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add this, alternating with flour and milk to well creamed mixture.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, and beat well after each one.
Mixture should be very creamy.
Put 1/2 cup cocoa and 2 cups of batter into small mixing bowl and mix together.
Put this with rest of batter by making swirl on top with knife.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours and 5 minutes.

title: "souper" burgers
directions: Preheat the grill to medium heat. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except buns. Mix well. Form into 6 equal-sized patties. Grill for 4 to 5 minutes per side or until the juices run clear and no pink remains. Serve on buns.

title: everlasting salad
directions: Mix lettuce and salt together and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain well and add carrot and green pepper.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Boil 4 minutes, then add to cabbage while hot.
Cool and refrigerate until served.

title: date pudding
directions: Place dates in mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water, sugar and butter.
Dissolve baking soda in hot mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pudding must be steamed in greased container for 2 hours.
Serve warm with hot sauce.

title: 2-step chicken broccoli divan
directions: In casserole dish, layer chicken, broccoli, soup and milk. Top with cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and oleo and sprinkle over top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash zucchini; slice off stem and blossom ends.
Cut zucchini in 1/4-inch pieces.
Boil in salted water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain well and mash.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and onion. Combine zucchini with egg mixture, corn and half of the cheese. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or rectangular baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until macaroni is tender, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a greased baking dish, place apple slices.
Add cinnamon, water and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix rest of sugar with flour and shortening until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven about 1 hour or until apples are tender and crumbs well browned.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.
(Serve hot with cream, hard sauce or ice cream.)

title: sugarless chocolate candy roll
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in top of double boiler.
Add milk and cook until very thick.
Remove from heat.
Add cracker crumbs, nuts, vanilla and butter.
Pour mixture on wax paper and form into rolls.
Roll in extra cracker crumbs and chill.
Cut in slices.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into eggs and then bread crumbs.
Heat oil and cook chicken until done.
Pour sauce into an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with pasta.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, cover and cube potatoes with cold salted water and bring to boil.
Drain potatoes and hold on side.
In roasting pan, heat the olive oil and rosemary.
Stir potatoes into hot oil and salt and pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir once.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix sugar with cinnamon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter Bundt pan, place nuts in pan.
Roll biscuit quarters in sugar mixture and place evenly around pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar and 1 to 3 tablespoons pancake syrup or corn syrup in pan on low heat, do not boil.
Pour brown sugar mixture on top of biscuit pieces.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and invert on platter.

title: pastry shell
directions: Mix flour and salt in medium bowl. Whisk oil and water together.
Pour over flour mixture. Stir with fork until blended. Pat evenly into a 9-inch pan, already sprayed with Pam.
Flute edge.
Prick bottom and sides at 1-inch intervals. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: my favorite cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley.
Refrigerate.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Make crust by crushing graham crackers and mixing with oleo. Press into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Crumble cheese in hot mixture and heat until cheese dissolves. Beat.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Whip milk until thick. Pour cheese and jello mixture into whipped milk and mix well. Pour over crust.
Chill.
Garnish with cherry pie filling or favorite garnish.
Can be frozen.
Serves 12.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix and place in 8 x 8-inch baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the shredded cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, chopped onion, 1/4 cup melted butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in the thawed hash brown potatoes.
Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: wine stew
directions: Mix wine, soup and soup mix in a 2-quart casserole or crock-pot.
Add stew meat and stir.
Cook at least 6 to 8 hours at 275° (until meat is tender) or in crock-pot on high.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Makes a wonderful alternative potato dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef strindberg
directions: Marinate beef with mustard. Sprinkle with salt and crushed peppercorns. Work finely chopped onions into tenderloin on both sides.
Heat a large skillet to 450° to 500° and add olive oil. Quickly sear meat on both sides so onions are golden brown. Remove tenderloin and arrange on plates (three to a plate).
Add butter to skillet, then add the mushrooms and saute to a light golden brown.
Add Chardonnay and reduce slightly.
Add cream and stir in fast.
Then sprinkle with parsley. Pour sauce over beef, which has been kept warm in the oven.

title: easy crackers
directions: Put crackers in paper grocery bag. Mix dry ingredients together and sprinkle over crackers. Close bag and shake well. Pour oil over cracker mixture and shake well. (Paper bag will become very greasy.) Empty into airtight container and enjoy.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Add salt and pepper to taste, butter and stale bread slices, slightly dampened.
Stir in slightly beaten eggs and about 1/4 pound cheese, cut in cubes. Add chopped onion and bell pepper.
Pour into a casserole, cover with bread crumbs or crushed crackers.
Dot with butter and bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: chocolate brownie cookies
directions: Beat butter, vanilla, sugar, brown sugar and eggs until creamy.
Mix flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda into mixture. Stir in 1 cup chips and 1 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well but do not beat.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: drop o' fruit cookies
directions: Soak fruits together. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Blend remaining ingredients.
Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Blend very well. Add fruit mixture and stir well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto nonstick baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef with green pepper and onion until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and mix with cooked noodles.
Pour into a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes to melt.

title: instant garlic bread
directions: Butter sliced bread lightly, but enough to cover entire piece. Sprinkle on garlic powder.
Turn toaster to medium heat.
Drop in; cook until butter is melted and bread lightly brown, about 2 1/2 minutes.
Cook too long, you'll have toast.
Cee ya.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with butter, soups, milk and rice.
Pour in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers over top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook broccoli and pepper until tender; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli and ground beef.
Top with crackers and butter.
Bake in 350° oven until hot through and through.

title: italian anise cookies
directions: Cream lard, Crisco, butter or margarine (whichever one you choose to use) and the sugar well.
Beat in the eggs.
Add the dry ingredients.
If sticky, refrigerate for 1 hour.
Separate into 4 sections.
Roll into a cylinder; cut diagonally across the cylinder with a knife before putting in the oven.
Do not cut through, just mark the cookies with the cut.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Makes 14 large cupcakes.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: philly 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Let cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased deep dish baker.
Press over bottom and halfway up sides with dough and pizza roller to form crust and seal perforations.
Slice sausages and arrange over crust.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over top.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl with whisk and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: bible puzzle cake
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a bowl mix well the dry ingredients.
Combine with the liquid mixture.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 large greased 9 x 12-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Rub salt, pepper and garlic powder into meat.
Rub flour on meat and brown in oil.
Place meat in roasting pan.
Pour over meat, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, cola and chili sauce. Bake at 325° for several hours.

title: peanut butter cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and salt.
Cook to a soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme first, then the peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: elegant apricot-sweet potatoes
directions: Wash apricots thoroughly and put in saucepan.
Add 2 cups of water.
Allow apricots to soak in covered pan for 1 hour, then cook in the same water that is simmering for 40 minutes until apricots are plump and tender.
Cool.
Drain, but reserve liquid.
Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain, cool, peel and cut lengthwise in 1/2-inch slices.
Grease 1-quart baking dish. Put in 1 layer of sweet potatoes.
Cover with layer of apricots, sprinkle with 1/2 of brown sugar.
Repeat layers with ingredients again.
Blend thoroughly the melted butter, orange juice and grated orange with 1/4 cup reserved apricot liquid.
Pour over potatoes. Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
About 5 minutes before removing from oven, top with pecan halves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite-size florets.
In a large bowl, toss broccoli, cheese, chopped onion and bacon.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and lemon juice. Pour over broccoli mixture.
Top salad with sliced fresh mushrooms and sliced boiled eggs.
Marinate overnight.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: *Fresh lemons are better but you can use the ReaLemon from bottle.
If you use fresh lemons, take from refrigerator several hours before using.
You get more juice if they aren't cold when you squeeze them.

title: spareribs and cabbage
directions: Start meat in enough water to cover.
When water begins to simmer, remove scum.
Simmer uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: minted mug
directions: Pour chocolate syrup into a warm mug and fill 3/4 full with coffee.
Top with scoop of vanilla ice cream and 1 jigger creme de menthe.
Serves 1.

title: old southern corn bread or muffins
directions: Combine flour, corn meal and sugar.
Add one tablespoon bacon drippings, buttermilk and eggs.
Leave 2 tablespoons in pan.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in melted butter, then in mixture of crumbs, cheese, garlic powder and salt.
Place in baking pan.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice parisian
directions: In skillet, brown lightly the rice and mushrooms in butter. Stir in soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Add water, a little at a time as pie crust.
Roll very thin.
Salt and cut into strips, then place on slightly greased cookie sheet and bake until light brown at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites well and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and add sugar gradually. Add butter and milk.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until filling is browned on top.
Makes 2 medium or 1 large pie.

title: chicken finger snacks
directions: Make 1 to 2 days ahead of time the honey mustard dip so it has time to let the flavors blend.
You do this by mixing honey and mustard together well and store in airtight container. Refrigerate.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat or in microwave.
Stir in brown sugar until well blended.
Stir in egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Do not overbake!
Cut into bars or squares while still warm. Serves 8.

title: casserole of chicken
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cottage cheese together. Start with layer of broccoli, layer of chopped chicken, grated cheese and sauce.
Another layer of broccoli, chicken, cheese and sauce.
Melt butter in skillet; saute bread crumbs.
Add more butter if needed.
Put buttered crumbs on top and cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: ruth's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil.
Add water; stir until mixture forms a ball.
Knead slightly with hands; divide into halves.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper to fit pie pan.
For cream pies, bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 6 mini loaf pans or 2 large loaf pans. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices and set pan aside. Beat sugars and oil until smooth. Add eggs and pumpkin to sugar mixture. Beat until smooth. Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk. Add pecans if desired. Place in loaf pans and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix the first five ingredients with spaghetti sauce or tomato sauce.
Cook pasta in large amount of salted water until tender. Layer in casserole with Mozzarella cheese.
Finish with sauce on top.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together in a skillet the Coca-Cola and catsup.
Skin chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in skillet.
Let it come to a boil; then reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: lemon icing
directions: Combine all to make spreading consistency.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first two ingredients together; add Cool Whip and mix well, then add strawberries and mix well.
Put in two graham cracker crumb crusts.

title: baby cockadoodle stew
directions: Blend or puree together; serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch dish; arrange croutons in bottom and sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Place over cheese and mushroom mixture.
Beat eggs, milk, soup and mustard.
Pour over all.
Bake at 300° until set for 1 1/2 hours.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated overnight and then baked.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over tossed salad.

title: bacon wrapped piggies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove casing from sausage links; cut each sausage and bacon slice into thirds and wrap bacon around pieces of sausage.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour brown sugar evenly over the sausage. Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 32 servings.

title: "shakertown" glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Mix together both sugars, lemon juice and melted butter.
Pour over carrots.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raving rice
directions: Cook and add together; let boil.
Then, turn to medium heat until almost all water cooks out of it.
Then cover with a lid and cook on low for 20 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar. Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Freeze in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo (room temperature mixes easier), cocoa and milk in small saucepan.
Bring to boil for about a minute and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: Cook Eagle Brand and cocoa for 5 minutes on low heat. Allow to cool slightly. Add next 3 ingredients. Refrigerate until cold. Mix in ice cream freezer. Halfway through, add nuts and marshmallows.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat Karo and oil in cast-iron skillet. Stir to mix.
Add pecans and salt thoroughly.
Place skillet in oven and bake 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from oven and place pecans on wax paper.
Separate pecans and salt thoroughly.
These become crisp as they cool.

title: hot mocha cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Store mix in an airtight container.
For each serving, place 2 tablespoons of mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.
Makes 44 servings, approximately 41 calories per serving.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, butter, soup and juice.
Pour on top of chicken.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into an ungreased loaf pan.
Sprinkle a few cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: spiced blueberry jam
directions: Combine blueberries, apple juice and lemon juice in an 8-quart stainless steel or enamel saucepan.
Place over high heat; stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Add honey, cinnamon and cloves. Continue stirring.
When mixture comes to a full boil again, begin timing for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Jam is ready when it is thick, jam like and sticks slightly to the bottom of the pan. Pour into hot, scalded half-pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Seal.
Process in a simmering water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 half pints.

title: date filled meringues
directions: Dates and nuts can be ground together in food processor.
In medium bowl, combine dates, nuts and vanilla flavoring, mix well. Shape 1/2 teaspoons of mixture into balls.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar until stiff peaks form.
Stir in flavor and food color.
Drop balls one at a time into meringue. Coat well to form 1-inch balls.
Remove with spoon and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan and cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Fix cake mix as instructed for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed.
While cake is still hot, punch holes all over the cake with a rounded pencil shape object.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the cake. Then pour caramel over the cake.
Pound Heath bars into small pieces.
Put 3/4 over cake.
Let cake cool in refrigerator. Then put your Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining Heath Bar pieces.
Keep refrigerated.
It's wonderful!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add additional pineapple juice if mixture appears dry.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced pear butter
directions: Pare and core pears; cut into 1-inch cubes.
To make 3 quarts, place in 5-quart kettle with vinegar and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, until soft, about 30 minutes.
Mash with potato masher or put through food mill.
Measure pulp.
There should be about 7 cups.
Return to kettle.

title: dilly carrots
directions: Boil carrots for 7 minutes; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Heat and serve.

title: brandied fruit
directions: In medium mixing bowl, put water, sugars and spices and mix. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils and sugars dissolve.
Stir once.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave 9 to 14 minutes or until fruit is tender. Stir 1 or 2 times.
Cover and refrigerate 3 days before serving.
Keep no longer than 3 weeks.

title: jello dessert
directions: Open milk; put in dish.
Freeze 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Mix sugar and pineapple together in pan.
Bring to boil.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and dissolve cream cheese in Jell-O mixture.
Let cool.
Whip canned milk with mixer and add Jell-O mixture.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut any fat away from the meat.
Mix together flour, salt and pepper; pound into both sides of meat.
Melt a small amount of Crisco in a skillet.
Brown steak thoroughly on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Slice bread in half the long way.
Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, oregano and tomato paste.
Spread half of coated meat on half of bread loaf.
Layer tomato slices and cheese slices alternately on top of meat.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese melts.
Do the same with the remaining mixture and other half of bread loaf.

title: sticky buns
directions: Cut 1 loaf of bread dough in pieces the size of a walnut.
Set aside.
Melt margarine.
Mix 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, vanilla pudding, cinnamon and milk.
Pour half of this melted mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place pieces of bread dough in pan.
Cut second loaf like the first and set aside. Pour remainder of melted mixture over pieces of dough in pan. Put cut pieces of second loaf on top of first.
Allow to rise until dough reaches top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Turn upside down on a cookie sheet.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, 1 cup Durkee fried onions and the Italian seasoning in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour bouillon over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken on top and pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Place vegetables around chicken covering rice.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until cooked.
Top chicken with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 1 minute or until onions are golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour; mix well.
Shape into small cookies (round ball shape).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: florentine crescents
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
