Combine spinach, cheese, bread crumbs and bacon in 1 1/2 quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cheese melts.
Unroll dough, separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise, forming 32 triangles.
Spread each triangle with approximately 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Roll up starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 32.

title: peach pickles
directions: Peel peaches into a solution of 1 gallon of water with 1 tablespoon salt and 2 tablespoons of vinegar.
This will prevent discoloring of peaches.

title: play doh(non-edible)
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in a saucepan. Add water and oil. Stir vigorously to blend. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the dough leaves the sides of the pan and is smooth. Add a few drops of food coloring.

title: brown rice
directions: Chop onion; brown in butter.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soup and sauce and hot sauce in large bowl.
Brown and drain meat.
Grease deep casserole dish.
Dip quartered tortillas in sauce.
Layer in casserole dish as follows: tortillas, meat, onion, cheese and olives until everything is gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: To a large pot, add water, salt, pepper and chicken; cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, debone and chop. Reserve 1 1/2 quarts of broth (add water, if necessary).
In a skillet, saute the peppers and onion in butter; add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and cheese and stir until blended.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, place in 9 x 13-inch dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Place corned beef brisket in Dutch oven; barely cover with hot water. Add onion, garlic and bay leaves. Cover; simmer 3 to 4 hours or until tender. Remove meat from liquid; keep warm.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and bring to boiling. Cook 5 minutes. Add cabbage wedges and cook 25 minutes longer.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat egg yolks, milk, flour, sugar, vinegar and salt. Cook until thick. While slightly warm, add marshmallows.
Let stand until cold.
Add whipped cream, nuts and pineapple.
let set overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook, cool and grate potatoes.
Combine potatoes with sour cream, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Top with herb seasoned stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put fruit in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with jello; add one cup sugar and water.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Drizzle butter over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.
When cool, refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat with mixer.
Mix together all dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add nuts if desired.
Spoon into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chips.
Needs no icing.

title: poor boy steak
directions: Layer beef, rice and soup mix in that order.
Mix together mushroom soup and water and pour over layers.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Cut biscuits in 4 to 6 pieces each, shake in bag. Put pieces in a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle leftover sugar on top.
Pour butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix Veg-All, soup and chicken together.
Pour into small casserole dish.
Cover with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbles.

title: maple-walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 20 muffin cups with paper liners. Toss the walnuts and butter together on a baking sheet and toast in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Keep the oven on.
Beat the eggs, cream, 1 cup of maple syrup and maple extract together in a mixing bowl.
Combine the flour, oats, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into egg mixture just until combined.
Stir in the dates and 1 cup of the toasted walnuts.
Fill each muffin cup 3/4 full with the batter.
Sprinkle the tops with the remaining walnuts and drizzle with the remaining syrup.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Poke a toothpick into the center of a muffin.
If it comes out dry, the muffins are done.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Beat eggs, add oil and beat well.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkle the chocolate chips on top and fold into top batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix together.
Let set a couple hours.
Then add the Cool Whip and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Set cream cheese out ahead of time to soften. Mix together mayonnaise and cream cheese. Add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Drain shrimp and mix well into mayonnaise mixture.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Put chips in bottom.
Add milk and butter.
Heat in microwave until soft.
Stir by hand.
Add nuts.
Put into buttered pan. Will harden in refrigerator.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in glass jar.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook noodles, but do not mix the seasoning packet with the noodles.
Butter a cookie sheet to put cooled and drained noodles on to cool.
Mix 1 package chicken seasoning mix with the mayonnaise.
Mix onions and celery into mayonnaise mixture.
Put noodles in a bowl and add mayonnaise mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs and chicken; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to box.
Bake in 2 round cake pans. While cake cools, prepare frosting.

title: apricot custard
directions: If desired, slice 2 apricot halves for garnish; set aside.

title: fried yellow corn
directions: Shuck and clean silks from corn.
Wash and drain.
Use sharp knife to cut and scrape corn from cobs into a wide open pan or bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour and about 1/2 to 1 cup of water. Blend well.
Slowly cook salt pork in cast-iron skillet to extract the grease.
Once grease is extracted, you can drain salt pork on a paper towel and nibble on it as you cook.
Remove grease from heat and slowly stir corn mixture into grease.
Return skillet to heat and cook over medium heat.
Add the stick of margarine, salt and sugar to taste and let simmer, stirring slowly, until corn is thick and the grease rises to the top (approximately 30 minutes).

title: good dill pickles
directions: Pack clean jars with whole or sliced cucumbers with 2 good sized bunches of fresh dill per jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a rolling boil and pour into jars with cucumbers in.
Seal with clean new lids.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix as instructed on box.
Mix nuts in mixture.
Pour cherries in 18-inch pan.
Pour cake mixture over cherries.
Bake at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate dumpling
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spoon batter over margarine; don't mix.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good over vanilla ice cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add chopped onions, tomato sauce and ketchup.
Simmer for an hour or longer, but not over 2 hours.
Beat eggs and add to cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: baked clams
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter for 4 minutes.
Steam clams in large pot of water until clams open.
Remove meat from shells (any clams that do not open, discard).
Grind clams in meat grinder.
Reserve clam shells.
Reserve water clams are cooked in. Remove celery and onion from stove.
Add clams, salt, pepper, thyme, parsley and sufficient bread crumbs to fill shells.
Add clam juice to make thick paste.
Fill shells and place strip of bacon on each.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Prepare and bake a pie crust.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to oil mixture and stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts.
Spoon into oiled pound cake
pan or oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 to 90 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix baking soda, molasses and boiling water.
Pour into two 8-inch pie pans.
Line with pastry.
Spread crumbs on top of pies. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Put 3 1/2 c. milk and add sugar (1/2 c. plus 2 Tbsp.) in 2 quart kettle.
Add salt, bring to boil, boil 1 minute.

title: holiday cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until cool.
Mold into balls and roll in chopped nuts. Mix with hands.

title: steamed fish
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Stir occasionally to blend, then put fish in steamer for 20 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, bringing to a boil, then add butter. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once and stir until moistened.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface; cut into 6-inch squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and boiling water and let stand 20 minutes - no longer. Cream butter or margarine with both sugars.
Mix with oatmeal mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Stir the soda, salt, cinnamon and flour together.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.

title: l.b.j. dry poultry seasoning
directions: Sprinkle this on chicken or any fowl before barbecuing.
Makes about 16 ounces.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil, then simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening and applesauce; beat 1 minute at low speed, just to combine.
At medium speed, beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Combine raisins and walnuts; fold into batter.

title: baked beans with sausage
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Saute onions and celery in butter 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients, except tomato paste.
Spread tomato paste across top.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: uninspired casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add onions, green pepper and tomatoes; simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; put in large casserole dish, cover and bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: coconut cake icing
directions: Boil until syrup makes soft balls in cold water.
Pour over egg whites, beating constantly.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with moist coconut.

title: baked chicken with orange nut rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart, greased, shallow baking dish. Coat chicken and
pout on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes	or
more.
If
rice
gets
too dry, mix a little water and
orange
juice and add during cooking.	Serve hot.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Cream the shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Using half of the dry ingredients, add cherry juice and milk and add remaining dry ingredients and creamed mixture.
Blend in melted chocolate, nuts and cherries.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cut 18 marshmallows in half and place on hot cookies. Cool and frost.
Top with nut or cherry half.

title: pineapple open-faced tarts
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Drain pineapple thoroughly and to the syrup add sugar and cornstarch mixture. Cook over low heat until thickened and clear, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Add butter and drained pineapple and stir until blended. Cool. Spoon into the 6 baked tart shells. Top with whipped cream and garnish with cherries.

title: speedy chili
directions: Cook beef, onions and pepper together until done.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili, pepper to taste and salt and simmer 5 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: speedy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Combine cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and hamburger mixture in large bowl.

title: "spanakopita" - spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and 1/2 cup butter, then cool.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients to eggs.
(Make sure the sauteed onion has cooled.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into greased casserole dish. Cover with cornflakes; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Make corn bread mix as usual and pour over mixture.
Mix and bake until brown.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make chicken broth.
I like using Spice Island chicken stock base.
Remove meat of potatoes and put in blender with salt, pepper, butter, sugar and chives.
Add a little broth and beat until liquid.
Add to rest of broth and cook gently for 5 minutes. Before serving, add 1 cup of cream and reheat.
Adjust salt to taste.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pork chops with mushroom pan gravy
directions: In 10-inch skillet cook bacon and onions over med. high heat, stirring occasionally, until browned (8 to 10 min).
Add pork chops, arranging bacon and onions on top of pork chops.
Cover; continue cooking for 10 minutes or until browned.
Turn pork chops. Reduce heat to med.
Cover; cook until pork chops are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Place pork chops on platter; keep warm while preparing gravy.
In same skillet with drippings, brown particles, bacon and onions add remaining ingredients except half and half., mushrooms and rice.
Cook over med heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and bubbly (1 min.)
Stir in half and half and mushrooms.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened (8 to 10 minutes).
Serve gravy over rice or noodles and pork chops.

title: orange slaw
directions: In a large bowl combine cabbage, carrots, oranges & green pepper. Set aside.

title: maxcine's meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat, onion, salt and pepper, celery powder and garlic powder and shape into small balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with small amount of oil.
Cover with water; add coffee, Kitchen Bouquet and dried onion flakes.
Salt and pepper to own taste.
Simmer on low burner until gravy thickens or may cook on low in oven.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter until lightly browned, 3 to 5 minutes. Set aside to cool.
Combine brown sugar, eggs and half and half in a saucepan.
Stir until it simmers.
Simmer 2 minutes and set aside.
Stir in whipping cream, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into ice cream canister.
Freeze in ice cream maker.
Makes about 1 quart. (Good!)

title: banana spice cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop dough by rounded spoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Lemon Butter Icing.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken and butter.
Dip chicken in butter.
Roll chicken in bread crumb and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: my skillet chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown chicken. Spoon off fat. Stir in soup and onions. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Remove chicken to platter. Keep warm. Stir in vegetables and sour cream into sauce over low heat. Heat, stirring constantly. Spoon some of sauce over chicken. Serve over noodles.

title: chantilly potatoes(servings: 4.  preparation time: 1 hour and 30 minutes.)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash with butter and 1/4 cup cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Whip the remaining 1/4 cup cream until stiff.
Spread mashed potatoes in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread whipped cream over the mashed potatoes; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 475° until the cheese melts and the top is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring water, potatoes, onions, ham, salt and pepper to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice until the potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes for flavor to develop.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut into chunks or strips.
Mix with soups, sour cream and 2 cups of cheese.
Fill tortillas with mixture.
Leave enough to spread over the top of rolled tortillas.
Place in casserole dish.
Spread leftover mixture over the top.
Top with 1 cup of cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.

title: dirt cups(fun for kids)
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon of crushed cookies into 8 to 10 paper or plastic cups. Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Decorate.

title: mustard toasted loaf
directions: Slice loaf lengthwise.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on bread.
Heat in a 425° oven until lightly browned.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Microwave 4 minutes or until hot.
Top with sliced almonds.

title: for fruit pies
directions: Mix.
Pour over berries in crust.
Stir around.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; remove bones and place in casserole dish.
Pour chicken soup over chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl and pour over chicken.
Pour chicken broth over and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: deep-dish cherry pie
directions: Drain syrup from dark cherries into 2 cup measure.
Drain tart cherries, adding enough of their juice to the dark cherry syrup to make 2 cups.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg in large saucepan.
Gradually stir in reserved juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles 1 minute.
Add cherries and butter.
Spoon into 8-cup shallow baking dish.

title: royal chicken bake
directions: Dip chicken in butter, then in mixture of flour, cheese, paprika and salt.
Place corn in bottom of shallow baking dish. Pour green chilies over this.
Arrange chicken on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and browned.

title: enchiladas
directions: Line pan with torn tortillas.
Add 1/3 chicken mixture, top with grated cheese; repeat procedure 2 times.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butter fingers
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Form with hands into finger shape cookies.
Bake at 375° on greased and floured pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Let margarine, eggs and sour cream stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Generously grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan; set aside.
Sift together flour, cocoa powder and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat margarine with a free-standing electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Gradually add sugars, beating about 10 minutes or until very light.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each and scraping bowl frequently.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately to beaten mixture, beating on low to medium speed after each addition just until combined.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine squash and onions. Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1 or 2 hours. Drain. Combine all other ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Add squash and onions and bring back to a rolling boil.
Make sure all squash is under liquid. Can and seal while hot.

title: critter chow
directions: Melt together the butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over 12 ounce box of crispy cereal.
Coat with powdered sugar and lay out flat about 5 minutes.
Then cut.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In deep, oven-safe dish, place chicken breasts on bottom, then sliced potatoes and then soup that has beef mixed with the milk. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add broccoli and bake 35 minutes more.

title: custard
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour in shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Cook and leave in pan (long cake pan). Take warm cake and make holes all over with toothpick.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam; pour rice and level in bottom of dish.
Lay chicken pieces over rice and salt and pepper. Mix soup and water; pour mixture over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: First Day:
Wash and slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick slices of cucumbers.
Soak in lime water 24 hours with enough water to cover.
Do not use metal pan.

title: monjo
directions: Boil beans to dry and add sugar to taste.
Mix all the ingredients together thoroughly except the boiled beans.
Make small balls of the mixed dough.
Flatten each ball wide and thin enough to fill each with spoons of sweetened beans.
Put ends of dough towards the center to close and place invertedly on greased baking pan (looks like stuffed buns). Dab with beaten egg yolk. Bake at 350° until dough is cooked.

title: zucchini stuffed with tomato-herb rice
directions: In large, heavy skillet, saute onion in butter 5 minutes or until soft and translucent.
Add rice; stir until coated with butter.
Stir in tomato paste until well blended.
Add broth, salt, pepper, parsley and basil.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes, then cool completely.

title: joanne's chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each one. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk to which you have added the vanilla.
Bake at 350°.
(Oven should be preheated.)

title: double crust fresh apple pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add apples, butter and flavoring mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg over mixture, trim excess crust, fold edges under and crimp. Put small slits in top crust.
Bake 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Put into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Top with strawberries, cherries or blueberries.

title: baked spinach and cheese
directions: Chop spinach into fine pieces.
Add parsley.
Cook in oil 10 minutes.
Add eggs beaten with milk.
Pour over spinach.
Turn in greased baking dish.
Add seasoning and cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Place uncooked macaroni in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour cooking oil over (just enough to lightly coat), then stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Velveeta, then stir.
Add milk, enough to come up sides of casserole and just over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Do not cover casserole during baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, mixed with cream of tartar, salt and baking soda.
Stir in cereal, oats, coconut and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten a little.
Bake on lower shelf of oven 5 to 6 minutes. Move to middle of oven and finish baking, about 5 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove from sheet and cool.
Two trays may be baked at the same time.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: pork and sweet potato stew
directions: About 2 hours before serving, peel sweet potatoes and cut into bite size chunks.
Cut green peppers lengthwise into 3/4-inch wide strips. Cut onions into bite size chunks. Cut each mushroom in half (or into quarters if large); mince garlic.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and chop or cut the strawberries into smaller pieces.
Then mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles. Fry hamburger with onions and mushrooms. Layer meat, noodles and then cheese. Repeat and bake about 30 minutes.

title: elsie's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all except first ingredient (the pie shell).
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Garnish with dollops of Cool Whip or real whipped cream. Eat and enjoy.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mrs. pierce's fruit cake
directions: Grease and line tube pans and mix ingredients all together. Bake in oven at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Decorate top with cherries cut in half and pecans about 1 hour before done.
Use wooden toothpick to test doneness.
Makes 2 tube pans and 1 loaf pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Divide the eggs. Mix egg yolks and cornstarch; beat thoroughly. Add milk. Put in double boiler; cool until thick. Remove from stove. Mix tablespoon butter and 1/2 cup coconut. Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white. Spread on pie crust; sprinkle coconut. Place in oven; bake until brown.

title: steamed fudge pudding
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in double boiler.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the eggs, milk, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and the melted chocolate.
Stir in bread cubes and nuts Turn chocolate mixture into an ungreased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place the filled baking dish into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish set on oven rack.
Pour boiling water into the large pan around the smaller dish to depth of 1-inch, being careful not to spill any water into the chocolate.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve pudding warm.
Cut into squares.
Top with whipped cream if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: weight watchers humdingers
directions: Stack ice cream and peanut butter on crackers to make sandwich.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze.

title: minute fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to bubble.) Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla; stir vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Let cool; cut into squares.
Garnish with nuts, coconut and crushed peppermint stick candy.

title: jamaican chicken
directions: Combine Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, rum, garlic and chives in a bowl. Wash and dry chicken and place in bowl with marinade, turning to coat both sides.

title: butter coconut pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 400° for 10 minutes. Combine sugar and flour. Stir in eggs, blending well. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until pie is set.

title: talon's trail mix(kids recipe)
directions: Mix all items together in a large bowl and store in an airtight container.
Take some in your school lunch or to the playground, but especially on camping trips.

title: frankie's surprise
directions: In a 15 x 9-inch oblong pan, press graham crackers and melted margarine into pan and allow to cool.
Pour container of Cool Whip onto crust.
Press sliced bananas into Cool Whip.
Drain crushed pineapple and pour over bananas and smooth out gently.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over pineapple.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over walnuts.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: gourmet peas
directions: Cook frozen peas in broth until barely tender.
Drain off liquid; reserve for later use.
Stir sour cream into peas; heat only until peas are coated and cream is hot.
Season to taste with salt.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt into big mixing bowl. In saucepan, mix and bring to a boil water, oleo and cocoa.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda, dissolved in buttermilk.
Pour batter into greased cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch approximate size).
Place in preheated 350° oven.
Bake about 20 minutes or longer.
After baking approximately 15 minutes, make the topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 cup of pecans to roll outside of ball.
Mix all ingredients; make into ball. Coat with pecans. Refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling evenly on the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple over cherries or apples.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pineapple. Cover the cake mix with the melted butter and top with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mike's crab dip
directions: Mix crabmeat and cream cheese.
Mix well and mold into meat loaf shape.
Mix horseradish and ketchup together to your own taste; spread over dip.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Surround by your favorite crackers.

title: pat's chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs and beat into the first mixture.
Add vinegar, vanilla and corn meal and mix well with all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(I bake pie shell for 5 minutes before adding the mixture.)

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need a punch bowl.

title: marinated roast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, blending well.
Place roast in shallow dish and pour marinade over roast.
Cover.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours, turning once.
Add roast, potatoes, carrots and marinade to baking dish and bake for 2 hours at 350°. Serve with pan drippings.
You can make gravy with some of the drippings, if desired.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In thick saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt and flour.
Add milk, vanilla and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Reduce heat and cook until thickened.
(This makes a thin syrup to serve over plain cake, etc.
To make a thicker syrup to serve over ice cream, increase flour to 4 tablespoons.)

title: paula's cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Spoon into paper-lined cupcake tins, 2/3 full.
Separately combine cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and chips and mix well.
Spoon 1 tablespoon on center of cupcake. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat; add beef and cook. Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender-crisp, not mushy.

title: noodle cheese pudding
directions: Boil noodles per package directions and drain.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, melted butter, sour cream, mashed cream cheese and vanilla.
Add noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into a large oblong baking dish that has been well buttered.
Spread topping over and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: palama-by-the-sea cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, then mix in flour and coconut.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheets about 1-inch apart.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with assorted chips, crackers or raw vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix eggs and sour cream together in one bowl.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese in another bowl.
Dip chicken in egg mixture then in bread crumbs.
Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix together, salt, baking powder, and sugar.
Add
enough milk to make a soft dough.
Place dough on top of melted margarine.
Spread evenly.
Pour fruit (which has been heated to boiling point) over the top of the dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with milk, cream, or ice cream.

title: pecan balls
directions: Beat butter or oleo 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup sifted powdered sugar and the vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Beat in flour; stir in pecans.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for about 18 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage
and cook in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Heat mushroom soup and stir until creamy.	Put 1/2 of
cabbage in casserole dish;	top with 1/2 of soup, 1 cup cheese and	1/2 of the crumbs.
Put in remaining cabbage, soup, cheese and	crumbs	in same manner.
Dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to
taste.
Top
with
onion rings.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: minestrone soup(low calorie)
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook carrots, zucchini, onion, and garlic in oil for 7 minutes until onion is tender.
Add the broth, V8 juice, garbanzo beans, tomatoes, green beans, and macaroni and basil. Bring to boil. reduce heat to simmer uncovered 15 minutes and stir in parsley.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until macaroni is tender.

title: baked lasagna casserole
directions: In large heavy pan, brown ground beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour.
Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Mix together eggs and cottage cheese.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook macaroni for 8 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water. Set aside.
Combine sugar, eggs, salt and flour with juices from fruits.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over cooked macaroni.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Before ready to serve, add Cool Whip; mix well, then add fruit and mix slightly.

title: grandma pocock's mincemeat
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer to desired thickness.
Put in sterile pint jars; seal and let stand 2 or 3 months to season.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring, then add to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour.
Mix soda and vinegar together and fold in carefully.
Bake in 9-inch pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: biscotti nocciole cioccolato(yields 3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place nuts in shallow pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
With paper towels, rub while warm to remove papery skins.
Grind nuts in processor until finely chopped.
Set aside.
Process chocolate coarsely.

title: beefy potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain. Add potatoes. Pour in dish. Add cheese. Place in microwave or oven until cheese melts. Eat!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayo and soup mix; stir well. Add chopped water chestnuts and scallions; stir.
Squeeze thawed spinach to remove all water; stir in spinach.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with rye bread, crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: pine cone bird treats
directions: Add peanut butter, bird seed and cornmeal to melted beef suet. Mix well. Roll pine cones with the mixture. Attach florist wire to the tops of the pine cones, about 1/2-inch down, for hanging outdoors.
Wire may be covered with yarn or ribbon.

title: easy salmon steaks
directions: Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Spray well with cooking spray.
Wash salmon steaks well and pat dry with paper towel. Arrange on broiler pan.
In small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon of mayo per steak and 1 tablespoon of ketchup per steak and lemon pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Spread over salmon.
Broil for 12 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave steaks in oven for another five minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Add flour, allspice, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and cocoa to all other ingredients.
Grate and add zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 to 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: buns
directions: Beat all ingredients until thick and then knead lightly.
Add flour until dough is soft and manageable.
Place in greased bowl, cover with towel and let rise until double in bulk.
Make into any kind of rolls.
Place on greased pans and let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes good cinnamon rolls, too.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Use medium grater on potatoes and onion.
Mix. Add unbeaten eggs; stir until blended.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well. Put enough shortening in skillet to make about 1/2-inch when melted.
When shortening is very hot, spoon in potato mix.
Use about 1/4 cup mix for each pancake.
Pat them lightly with a spoon to spread to desired thickness.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Shred peeled potatoes or cube and food process to mush.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add egg and 1 cup of flour; blend to make a batter.
(If too soupy, add flour by 1/2-cup increments.)
Pour out onto hot griddle to form pancakes.
Flip when edges appear gray and firm.
Brown gently.
Serve with butter, sausage and kraut.

title: claussen clone pickles
directions: Fill 5 quart plastic pail (with cover) with pickles standing on end, dill at top and bottom of pail, onion, garlic and mustard seed.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook salt pork until crisp.
Remove any lean pieces of pork; save.
Add the potatoes, 1 1/2 cups of water, onion and clam liquor to drippings.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add clams, 1 3/4 cups milk and the cream.
Blend together 1/4 cup milk and flour; stir into chowder. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and salt pork.
Serves 6.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put water, cloves and cinnamon in kettle.
Bring to a boil; turn heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Turn heat off; add tea bags and seep 7 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add sugar, orange juice concentrate and lemon.
Stir; use a fine strainer and strain the teas.
(Can be frozen.)
Great in the winter.

title: jim's coconut cream pie(club member: renee evans)
directions: Combine ingredients, except coconut. Cook until thick over low heat. Add coconut to filling. Top with Cool Whip. Makes 2 pies.

title: pinch-me-cake
directions: Set aside 1 package dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Heat milk.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, salad oil and salt.
Add hot milk to sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast and egg.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well with wooden spoon.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour and mix until well blended and satiny.
Let rise until at least double.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Melt butter and roll balls in this, then roll in mixture of 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Drop in angel food pan.
Let rise until at least double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried onions
directions: Slice onions into thin rings.
Heat broth over high heat in wok or heavy skillet.
Add the onions.
Stir-fry until tender. Sprinkle with ground pepper.

title: hungarian beef goulash
directions: Cut beef into serving pieces. Season lightly. Brown onion in butter or margarine.
Add paprika and beef and brown lightly on all sides. Add stock. Cover and simmer until almost done. Add potatoes, cut in quarters, carrots and celery. Cover and cook slowly until done.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Add all ingredients plus 2 cups cold water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Knead until smooth; keep covered.

title: dreamy spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute beef in 1 tablespoon butter until brown.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green onion and green pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole, spread half of the spaghetti.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add remainder of spaghetti.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over spaghetti and spread tomato meat sauce on top.
Chill thoroughly.
Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This recipe may be assembled the day before and stored in refrigerator until time to remove for baking.

title: whole wheat doughnuts
directions: Combine buttermilk, butter,
eggs
and vanilla in large bowl, beating well.
Combine
flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking powder, soda
and
salt.
Add
to
buttermilk
mixture, mixing well.
Place dough	on
floured
surface;
roll out 1/4 inch thickness.	Fry in deep
fat.
Glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons water and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan; pour in cherry pie filling and pineapple, including juice, and mix with fork.
Dump cake mix on top of fruit mixture. Slice butter and put on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: potato and ham pie
directions: For filling, combine together in mixing bowl:
eggs, vegetables, meat, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, milk and onion; set aside. Combine shredded potatoes and 1/2 cup cheese.
Press into bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Pour filling into potato-lined pie plate.

title: squaw corn with squash
directions: In large skillet, saut onions, garlic and squash in oil. Stir in green chili and corn. In a 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish, layer the vegetables, tortillas and cheese (1 cup). Pour soup over all and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Put a slice of cheese on top of each chicken piece, then put the soup on top of chicken and cheese.
Combine stuffing with melted butter; sprinkle on chicken. Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake for an additional 1/2 hour.
Serve with white rice.

title: warren heistand's carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add the sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, drained pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Place cherry pie filling mix in a buttered 9 x 12 pan.
Mix cake mix, coconut and chopped nuts and spread evenly over cherries. Drizzle butter over dry cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut; place in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour on top of pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Pour this mixture on top of cake mix and spread.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg yolks and blend thoroughly.
Beat whites until stiff, then fold in.
Gradually add water and tomatoes.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend with creamy mixture.
Bake in two greased and floured round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with your favorite butter frosting and top with strawberries.

title: herb chicken stew
directions: Poach chicken in just enough water to cover.
Remove chicken from stock.
Set aside chicken to cool.
Reduce stock by rapidly boiling 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and garlic to stock. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add carrots and seasonings*; simmer 10 minutes or until carrots are barely tender.
Add potatoes, whole or quartered.
Simmer until barely tender.
Add chicken and zucchini.
Stir in nutmeg just before serving.
Great with crusty brown bread!

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Sprinkle pecans into two greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Cut dough into 1 inch pieces and arrange over pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour evenly over dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts one hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plates.
Yield:
Two 9-inch coffee cakes.

title: can't leave alone pudding
directions: Melt in a 13 x 9-inch pan butter or margarine.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture over butter or margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour favorite fruit over mixture. Don't stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend well and refrigerate until ready to serve, at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Great summertime treat!

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soup mix, tomato juice, water and
seasonings.
Simmer
for
5 minutes.
Add rice and vegetables and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: apple slices
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix egg yolk with milk and stir into flour mixture.
Pat half the dough in a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Pour apples over dough.
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Roll remaining dough on floured surface to fit pan.
Place over apples.
Brush with egg white and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing while warm.

title: divine divinity
directions: Bring sugar, vanilla, water and salt to a boil over medium heat.
Cook to softball stage, 240°.
Beat into marshmallow cream on high speed until it loses the glossy color.
Pour into square pan.
When cool, cut into small squares.
Can add nuts, if desired.

title: baste for fillet
directions: Melt butter and add all other ingredients.
Smear on fillet. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 45 minutes for rare, 1 hour for medium.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.

title: pepper pot stew
directions: Cut beef into one inch (2 1/2 cm) cubes.
Cover meat with flour and brown on all sides in hot oil.
In large saucepan, add salt and stock and cook covered for about 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Add vegetables, pepper and parsley and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: american chop suey
directions: In a large frying pan melt margarine, add hamburg, onions and garlic.
Brown and continue cooking on low heat.
Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Then, add cooked, drained elbows to hamburg mixture.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and cook on low heat 30 to 60 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in food coloring; set aside.
Drain grated cucumber on paper towels, gently squeezing out excess moisture.
Fold into cream cheese mixture and set aside.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together graham crackers, margarine and powdered sugar; press into pan.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter; pour into cups.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, salt and cocoa in large saucepan. Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir; add oats last.
Stir and drop quickly onto wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: tofu burgers
directions: Mash the tofu well.
Chop celery very fine.
Mix all ingredients well and form into 2 to 3-inch patties.
Roll each patty in breading mixture of last 3 ingredients.
Fry in skillet with 1/4-inch oil.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper.
Serve hot on a bun with garnishes or plain.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and spices.
In another bowl, combine the eggs and potatoes, then beat in the dry ingredient mixture to make a stiff dough.
Roll the dough out on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of about a half inch.
With a knife, cookie cutters or the rim of a glass, cut into shapes. Fry in deep fat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain on clean, absorbent cloths.

title: pralines
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, salt, and milk.
Cook to softball stage (test by dropping a little in water or use candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
While this is cooking, caramelize (until brown) sugar in a small, thick skillet.
Combine with above mixture until it reaches test stage and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans and beat.
Before candy crystallizes, dip out by separate spoonfuls and place on waxed paper to cool.
If mixture should crystallize too soon (before removing from saucepan), add a Tbsp. of boiling water and beat again.
Yields 24 pralines.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: squash apple scallop
directions: Peel squash, slice in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut into slices.
Place in a saucepan with water and salt.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes; drain.
Layer squash and apple slices in a 1-quart greased casserole.
Combine sugar, corn syrup, orange juice and orange rind.
Pour over squash and apples.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: big cookie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add chocolate chips.	Using a large pizza
pan	(greased), pat mix out.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut each squash into halves; remove seeds and fibers.
Pare squash; cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Arrange squash in ungreased oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches).
Top with apple slices. Sprinkle sugar mixture over top.
Cover and cook in 350° oven until squash is tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and put in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Cover with foil while baking. Uncover last 5 minutes to crisp cracker topping.

title: diet dippity dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with a large platter of raw mixed vegetables.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
In a large mixer bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Make a well in the center.
Add oil, egg yolks, peel, vanilla and 3/4 cup cold water.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until combined.
Then on high speed, mix about 5 minutes or until satin smooth.
Thoroughly wash beaters.

title: cuban-style black beans
directions: I put onions, garlic and bell pepper in food processor to chop.

title: gooey brownies
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 pan, this will also grease the pan.
Pour melted butter in mixing bowl with other ingredients, pour into the 8 x 8 baking pan.

title: french silk pie
directions: Whip butter for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and whip an additional 5 minutes.
Melt the chocolate, then cool completely.
Add chocolate to butter/sugar mixture.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Once all eggs are mixed well, add vanilla.
Place mixture into pie shell and chill for 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cabbage chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery in Dutch oven sprayed with Pam.
Add V-8 juice, broth, chili powder and cabbage.
Cook until cabbage is done.
Serve with chopped onion, shredded cheese, fresh parsley and whole wheat crackers.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion together until almost done and drain.
Add tomatoes and let bubble.
Put beans in casserole and add meat mixture.
Mix corn meal mix as directed.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes a large casserole dish.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, salt, onion and garlic. Gently fold in the diced potatoes.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and sprinkle on the paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It will be lightly browned on top.
Serves 6.

title: apple, raisin, walnut muffins
directions: Mix apples with sugar.
Next, take liquids and stir together and pour over apples.
Mix together dry ingredients and pour over apple mixture.
Mix slightly.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour in greased muffin tins, 2/3 or 3/4 full.
Makes 16 muffins.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside down surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 9x13 pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over bottom of the pan. Combine cake mix, oil and eggs. Beat at low speed until moistened. Beat another 2 minutes on high. Spoon batter to with in one inch of edges. Bake for 43-53 minutes. or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm or cold. Store in refrigerator.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Place
tomatoes
in
baking
dish that has been covered with fine
bread crumbs 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Sprinkle onion, bell pepper and seasonings over tomatoes.
Drizzle butter over all. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Place in large bowl.
Add eggs and butter; mix well.
Make sure spaghetti is hot (this will cook the eggs).
Saute onion in olive oil until tender; stir in spaghetti mixture.
Add bacon bits and Parmesan cheese; mix well. Serve with tossed salad.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop corn--remove all unpopped kernels.
Place all ingredients in largest bowl (popcorn, m&m's, peanuts).
Melt butter in heavy pan on stove.
Add marshmallows & dissolve slowly (low heat).
Pour over ingred. in bowl.
Stir until syrup covers all.
Butter angel food tin & place all popcorn, etc in pan.
Pack down tightly.
Be near sink.
Keep hand cool with cold water.
Put in fridge or freezer until ready to use.
Slice with serrated knife.

title: oven fried turkey
directions: Sprinkle turkey pieces with salt and pepper.
Dip in butter, then roll in stuffing crumbs.
Place pieces, skin side up, in a jelly roll pan or other shallow pan.
Drizzle with 1/2 of the remaining butter, then sprinkle with the remaining crumbs.
Cover with foil.

title: banana nut crunch
directions: Mix together chopped pecans, egg and sugar.
Spread on greased foil sheet; bake at 350° until brown.
Set aside to cool.
Stir together package of vanilla pudding mix and milk.
Add sour cream and whipped topping.
Using a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer 1/2 of the nut mix and sliced bananas, pudding mixture, and the rest of nut mix on top.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
This is an elegant version of old fashioned banana pudding.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients, divide into 3 parts, shape into rolls on shiny side of foil.
Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Poke holes in bottom of foil.
Place on rack with pan under to catch drippings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato crisp
directions: In a large, heavy, disposable aluminum pan, mix well all the ingredients except the chips and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread evenly.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Serve with garlic crackers.

title: harvest bean bake
directions: Saute onion
and
green
pepper in small amount of oil. Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain fat.
Add to this mixture,
beans,
soup,
mustard,
salt, Worcestershire sauce, thyme and
pepper.	Put
into
quart greased casserole.	If desired, arrange
apple
slices brushed with oil on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, seasoning mix, stewed tomatoes and green peppers.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Place 1/2 of mixture in dish.
Top with cheese.
Add all tortillas, cut up in bite-size pieces.
Add rest of mix.
Top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon in Dutch oven.
Drain and rinse in colander.
Return to kettle.
Add onion and saute until tender. Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Add to kettle along with other ingredients.
Simmer to blend flavors.
Works well in crock-pot.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch cake pan, put in layers of pie filling, dry cake mix, coconut and nuts.
Pour on melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken ole
directions: Combine taco sauce, mustard and lime juice.
Marinate chicken in mixture at least 30 minutes.
Melt margarine in skillet. Remove chicken from marinade and brown in skillet about 10 minutes on each side.
Add marinade and cook until chicken is tender and marinade glazes chicken.
(Low-fat recipe.)

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients
and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In
saucepan,
add
broth, celery and onion.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Hold
strainer over boiling broth and pour eggs into strainer,
making
sure
to stir broth all the while egg comes through
strainer.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hootenany cake
directions: Grease bottom of Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, mix cake mix, pudding, water, eggs, oil, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon together. Put 1/3 of nut mixture in bottom of pan, then half of cake batter.
Add 1/3 nut mixture and remaining cake batter.
Finish with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mash corned beef.
Add onions, bell pepper and mayonnaise; stir.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.
Salt and pepper.
Makes 8 whole sandwiches.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour or until custard is set and top lightly browned.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and celery fine.
Cook in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients (except hot dogs) and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour mixture over hot dogs in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef quiche
directions: Brown beef with onion and green pepper.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese; add to the meat mixture.
Put into crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla. Add flour and nuts.
Mix well. Form into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: abadie's amaretto
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes. Remove from heat; cool.
Remove lemon peel.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Butter bread lightly and pull apart.
Layer bread and cheese in baking dish (9 x 13-inches or 2 1/2 to 3-quart).
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes over water.

title: mocha milkshake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until foamy.
Slowly add enough ice cubes to bring mix to the three-cup line.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately. Yields 3 cups (88 calories per 1 cup serving).
Contains 5.2 g protein, 0.3 g fat, 15.2 g carbohydrate, 3 mg cholesterol, 82 mg sodium and 188 mg calcium.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in large, heavy boiler.
Bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Set boiler in cool water and beat until thick and glossy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut when set.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Blend in the egg.
Sift the salt, flour and baking powder together; add to mixture.
Blend the vanilla into the mixture.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Get grease real hot before starting.
Blend egg and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Coat hot dog with the mixture and fry in hot grease.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Press 3 to 4 additional M&M's into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Cook meat, onion, broth and seasonings in slow cooker on 250 degrees for 8 hours until meat is tender.

title: green chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes before serving to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter-butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the butter until creamy, then slowly add the brown and granulated sugars, and continue beating until well blended.
Add the eggs and beat until smooth and light, then add the peanut butter and mix well.
Pour the flour into the peanut butter mixture, then sprinkle on the baking soda and salt. Beat until all ingredients are well mixed.

Roll spoonfuls of the dough between the palms of your hands into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter, and place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Press each cookie with the back of a fork, pressing first in one direction then the other, to make a crosshatch design and flatten each cookie to a round, about 1 1/2 inches across and 1/3 inch thick.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the edges are slightly brown.

title: onion pie
directions: Pour melted margarine into the cracker crumbs and press into a pie pan to make a crust.
Saute the onions in the 2 Tbsp. of margarine for about 10 min.
Pour the onions over the crust. Slightly beat the eggs and milk and pour over the onions. Sprinkle the cheese over the top.
Bake 30 - 35 min. at 350°.
Let set 5 min. before serving.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Mix tomatoes, mixed vegetables and beef broth in pot.
Add ground chuck and onion.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow peanut treats
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and milk in a double boiler.
Add peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix fast and well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and store in airtight container.

title: vinegar cobbler
directions: Mix water, sugar, nutmeg and vinegar.

Set on stove to heat. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and butter with enough milk to make biscuit dough consistency. Roll on floured board to about 1/8-inch thick. Cut a piece the size of top of cobbler pan.
Cut remaining dough in 2-inch strips.
Cover bottom of buttered pan with strips, then pour some of the hot liquid mixture.
Put in another layer of dough strips; pour in remaining liquid. Cover with dough reserved for top. Cut slits in crust.
Brush with mixture of butter and sugar.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake in a 400° oven until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter, cocoa, vanilla and salt in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in peanut buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let stand until firm. Cut into squares.
Yields 36 servings.

title: quick double fudge cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar in bowl.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Blend well.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes in long pan.
Frost with Fudge Icing.

title: whole wheat zucchini bread
directions: Sift all-purpose flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Beat eggs, oil, honey and lemon extract with rotary beater until smooth and frothy.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour mixture; stir well, but do not beat.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 1 loaf.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, 1/2 c. water, the onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded Tbsp. in 12 balls.
Cook meatballs in 10 inch skillet until brown on all sides.
Drain.

title: meemie's coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and oleo (room temperature) with a fork.
Add eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut evenly on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: *Use the 46 ounce bottles or frozen concentrate mixed according to package directions to make the 46 ounces.

title: cheese dip
directions: Fry and drain meat.
Mix ingredients in pan or crock pot. Heat and serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender; cool and tear into small pieces. Add crushed pineapple and almond slivers; add mayo to consistency you want. Add sugar to taste and vinegar.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Melt cheese and 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan, stirring often until smooth.
Place vegetables into a 1-quart casserole dish. Pour cheese over vegetables; mix well.
Melt remaining butter; stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat until the mixture becomes clear and bubbly.
Watch closely, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and pour over a large angel food cake that has been torn into small pieces and placed in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover and allow to chill for 24 hours.
Serve with a scoop of whipped cream.
Great dessert and simple to make.

title: low calorie chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave on High 30 minutes.

title: stewed rhubarb
directions: Cover rhubarb with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Meanwhile, make a syrup with the other ingredients.
Add drained fruit and cook until tender.
Also good with strawberries added.

title: easy and delicious turkey breast
directions: If frozen, thaw turkey breast as per packaging directions. Place turkey in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over turkey.
Cover.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove turkey breast.
Let stand for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1
quart
casserole,
arrange layers of beans alternately with
mushroom
soup,
onions,
almonds and cheese. Add dash of pepper; top with sprinkling of bread crumbs or Parmesan cheese. Bake
in
350° oven 20 minutes or until bubbling. Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix altogether and place in a covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potluck vegetable casserole
directions: Combine creamed corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in drained vegetables.
Turn into 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt oleo. Toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix together and place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Add salt, pepper
and onion to meat.
Brown lightly and drain. Put hamburger
mixture
in casserole dish.
Pour soups over it. Add Tater Tots and bake at 300° until brown.

title: berry lemon trifle
directions: Divide the angel food cake cubes among 4 dessert dishes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo and 1/3 cup condensed milk. Spread 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup condensed milk. Sprinkle chocolate chips, then spread the chocolate mixture. Dribble rest of cake batter over all and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and set aside.
Mix eggs and buttermilk well.
Dip chicken into milk and egg ingredients, then roll into the flour and drop into a skillet of hot cooking oil.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef until good and done!!
Add tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Put 1/2 of the noodles in buttered casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture onto noodles.
Put rest of noodles on top.
Pour hamburger mixture all over the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown the sausage and set aside.
Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart saucepan (a Dutch oven works best).
Bring it to a boil and cook just until vegetables are tender-crisp.
In a small dish mix 1/4 cup cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to the vegetable and meat mixture.
Cook just until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: crab, cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cheese. Add mayonnaise and soup.
Stir until smooth. Saute crabmeat and add.
Also add garlic and other seasoning. Makes about 2 cups.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together 5 minutes, then add confectioners sugar.
Beat until ready to spread.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of cooking oil.
Add beef, onion and pepper.
Brown very slightly and salt to taste.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and pimiento.
Place in attractive baking dish and top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are cooked all the way through and brown (20 to 25 minutes).
Add sliced mushrooms if desired.

title: viola watkins' good salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Put ingredients in salad bowl in layers in order listed, with cheese on top.
Cover tightly and leave in refrigerator overnight. Before serving, toss gently with two forks or salad utensils. This good and crunchy salad will keep well in the refrigerator for several days.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch nonmetal baking dish, spread 1 can of the ravioli.
Mix egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan, parsley and garlic powder.
Spoon over ravioli.
Top with half the cheese slices.
Spoon remaining ravioli over; top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: farmer's salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, except salad dressing or mayonnaise, sugar and cheese, in layers in a cake pan.	Combine salad dressing or mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top of layers.	Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill 24 hours before serving.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Stir together in a bowl and put in an uncooked pie shell. Add 3 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn down heat to 350° and bake until brown.

title: rainbow delight cake
directions: Cool cake; split to make 3 layers.
Whip the cream and add the sugar.
To 1 cup whipped cream, stir in green food color and almond extract.
Fill first and second layers.
To 1 cup cream, stir in yellow food coloring and rum flavoring.
Fill second and third layers.
Tint remaining 2 cups whipped cream with red food color and stir in peppermint extract.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of the pan. Sprinkle celery on top of lettuce, then green pepper, onion and peas.

title: homestyle baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Add onion and brown; drain.
Mix chili sauce, molasses, Gravy Master, garlic powder, mustard and vinegar in a bowl.
Add beans.
Mix in bacon and onion.
Cook on stove 1 1/2 hours on low flame; stir often.
Serve hot.

title: toasted coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Blend in buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Toast coconut in a 200° oven; cool.
Add to mixture.
Chill for about 10 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain salmon.
Discard bones and skin.
In a processor or blender, mix all ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Blend until smooth.
Turn into quiche dish or crock, spreading evenly. Refrigerate.

title: country style corn chowder
directions: Fry diced bacon until brown and crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and set aside.
Saute onion and potatoes in bacon drippings.
Add corn, broth (herbal brand okay) and seasonings.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Then stir in whipping cream and bacon. Heat through and serve.

title: living skills biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or fork.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll out onto floured board.
Cut out.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Remove	bone
from
chicken breast, cut in half lengthwise. Put the chicken breast between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and
pound until about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and parsley. Chill
stick
of
butter;
when chilled, cut in 8 sections. Place
section
of butter in each end of chicken fillet.
Roll up	and
secure with toothpick.
Roll each with plain flour and dip in mix of 1 beaten egg and 1 tablespoon of water and
roll in package of bread crumbs.
Chill for 1 hour. Deep fry for about 5 minutes or until browned well.

title: mary's chicken salad
directions: Remove chicken from bones.
Chop all ingredients in food processor until fine but not pasty.
Add mayonnaise only until salad holds together in a clump.

title: gail's shameless tarts
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Spoon mixture into small foil midget cups 3/4 full and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
While cooling, mix sour cream, 1/4 cup of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon into cream cheese mixture.
Cook again at 325° for 5 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Before serving, add fruit pie filling.
Cherry and blueberry pie filling do best.

title: yeast rolls(simple to make, good)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, Crisco and flour.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator about 15 minutes. This will keep several days in refrigerator.
Bake as desired.

title: taco squares
directions: Spread out can of crescent rolls on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cook tomatoes, meat and seasonings together.
Spread on top of rolls and then spread cheese on top. Then put other can of crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown, about 35 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: taco lasagna(for microwave)
directions: Serve with salsa or sour cream.

title: mamaw's hot potato salad
directions: Cook, cool and slice potatoes.
Chop onion and mix with mayonnaise.
Crumble bacon and grated cheese.
Mix well. (Sprinkle some cheese on top.)
Slice olives over top and pour bacon drippings on top.
Put in oven and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in cake.
Pour the can of Eagle Brand milk and the cream of coconut over the cake so it will soak into it.
Let the cake cool completely, then put the Cool Whip over the cake and sprinkle coconut over the cake.
Place in refrigerator.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk; refrigerate 1 hour.
Add all the other ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: sugar crust cake
directions: Whip Crisco, adding sugar gradually until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then the flour.
Beat until smooth, adding lemon and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, spice and salt in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, evaporated milk and egg until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in 375° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Mix together and add to egg, the flour and sugar.
Add milk to egg, flour and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, melted butter or margarine and raisins.
Mix all together and put in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt together marshmallows and 1/2 cup margarine.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put 3/4 mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 bag marshmallows over mixture.
Melt together caramels, condensed milk and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour over Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Put on remaining Krispies.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars with egg.
Combine and beat in until smooth next 3 ingredients.
Sift together and add to mixture next 5 ingredients. When beaten smooth, add oatmeal.
Beat mixture well.
Drop cookies 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine water and spaghetti sauce. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Layer noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella. Sprinkle Parmesan. Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, and put in a greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple and whip the whipping cream.
Cream together powdered sugar.
Then add pineapple and pecans.
Mix.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into baked shell or graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies.
Mix per instructions and let cool.
Crumble 1/2 of the brownie in bowl (use a punch bowl).
Mix large chocolate pudding per instructions and pour over brownie mix.
Add Three Musketeers candy bars broken up in bite size pieces.
Next spread 1/2 of the large Cool Whip on top of candy bars.
Crush 1 Butterfinger candy bar and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Repeat the above for the 2nd layer.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix together cabbage and onion.
In a jar shake together sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and the flavor packet from noodles.
Pour on the cabbage and chill.
When ready to serve, crush the noodles (do not cook) and add along with the sunflower seeds and almonds to cabbage mixture.
Toss and serve.

title: custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add to all other ingredients (but eggs). Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch well-buttered pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: In a glass baking dish spread refried beans on the bottom. Mix sour cream and Ranch mix together and continue layering.
When finished this dish can be served hot or cold with tortilla chips.

title: microwave-herbed potatoes
directions: Make crosswise cuts
1/2 inch apart in each potato, not cutting all the way
through.
Place
an
onion
slice in each cut.
Place
potatoes in 2-quart microwavable casserole.
Cove and microwave on High (100%) until potatoes are almost tender, 4 1/2 minutes to	5 1/2 minutes.	Microwave margarine in 1 cup microwavable measure on
High
(100%) until melted, 30 seconds to one minute.
Stir
in
remaining
ingredients; drizzle over potatoes.
Cover and
microwave
on High (100%) until potatoes are tender 4 to 5 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 15 minutes.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake 20 minutes at 400° in greased baking dish.

title: french pepper bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° about 40 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Mix flour with cold milk; add this to hot milk and stir until thick and smooth.
Add bread crumbs, grated or chopped cheese, pepper and salt.
